(453, 0, 'Strange Moments Two Cats Disappear At Aba Market [Video]', 'Metro News', 'https://www.informationng.com/2019/10/strange-moments-two-cats-disappear-at-aba-market-video.html', 'https://www.informationng.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/cat.jpg', 'Cat\nA CCTV footage has shown the mysterious moment two cats disappeared at a market in Aba, Abia state.\nIn the video shared via Twitter, two cats were seen strolling through an empty corridor of shops, when they suddenly disappeared at the same time.\nHowever, some social media users have argued that the video might have been tampered with, while some are of the firm belief that the cat really disappears.\nRead Also: Brides Catches Groom Sexually Assaulting Her Bridesmaid; Goes Ahead To Marry Him\nSee video below\n\n&#8211; CCTV captures the moment two cats disappeared at a market in Aba ,Abia state. pic.twitter.com/InUeGnQi4v\n&mdash; SubDeliveryZone (@SubDeliveryZone) October 21, 2019\n\nThe post Strange Moments Two Cats Disappear At Aba Market [Video] appeared first on Information Nigeria.\n', 0, 'Mon, 21 Oct 2019 15:16:48 +0000'),
(454, 0, 'Mungo Park Didn’t Discover Source Of River Niger, Stop The Brainwash: Reno Omokri', 'Education', 'https://www.informationng.com/2019/10/mungo-park-didnt-discover-source-of-river-niger-stop-the-brainwash-reno-omokri.html', 'https://www.informationng.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Reno-book-signing-700x466.jpg', 'Popular social media activist, Reno Omokri has queried the decision of curicculum makers over the teaching that Mungo Park discovered the source of River Niger.\nNigerian author, Reno Omokri\nAccording to the activist, the common saying that Mungo Park discovered the source of River Niger is a historical lie.\nAlso Read: Reno Omokri Helps Victim Of Onitsha Fire Outbreak (Video)\nHe went further to express that the continuous teaching of that knowledge in school is a deliberate attempt to brainwash Nigerians.\nSee his post below:\n\nWhy does Nigeria still allow that colonial historical lie that Mungo Park discovered the source of the River Niger to be taught in schools? How can Nigeria continue to brainwash her own children with a colonial lie?\n                  #TableShaker#FreeLeahSharibu #RenosNuggets\n&mdash; Reno Omokri (@renoomokri) October 21, 2019\n\nThe post Mungo Park Didn&#8217;t Discover Source Of River Niger, Stop The Brainwash: Reno Omokri appeared first on Information Nigeria.\n', 0, 'Mon, 21 Oct 2019 15:13:41 +0000'),
(455, 0, 'Prophet Jailed For Stealing Member’s International Passport', 'Metro News', 'https://www.informationng.com/2019/10/prophet-jailed-for-stealing-members-international-passport.html', 'https://www.informationng.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/court-jails-woman-for-exposing-her-cheating-boss-who-was-having-affair-with-a-colleague.jpg', '\nA Prophet in Zimbabwe has been sentenced to 6 months in prison after he stole the passport of a member of his congregation and used it to travel to South Africa under the falsehood that he was praying for it.\nThe prophet identified as Shepherd Mbili was convicted by a Bulawayo Magistrate, Zimbabwe after he pleaded guilty to the charges levelled against him.\nRead Also: Photos, Details Of Lady In Viral Video With Pastor Wilson Emerges Online\nThe prophet was said to have asked Mr Godknows to bring his passport and academic certificates for anointing, he then prayed for it and advised the complainant not to open the envelope fully knowing that he had stolen his passport.\n“He told me not to open the envelope until I’m ready to use it On the 6th of October I opened the envelope to check the last date I went to Zambia and I found out that my passport was missing. I went to look for Prophet Mbili and his wife told me that he had travelled to South Africa with my passport and would be back soon” said the congregant whose passport was stolen.\nThe post Prophet Jailed For Stealing Member&#8217;s International Passport appeared first on Information Nigeria.\n', 0, 'Mon, 21 Oct 2019 15:11:58 +0000'),
(456, 0, 'Wizkid Gushes About 3rd Babymama, Jada Pollock', 'Entertainment', 'https://www.informationng.com/2019/10/wizkid-gushes-about-3rd-babymama-jada-pollock.html', 'https://www.informationng.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/b7Zk9kpTURBXy9lZjY3ZWIxMDc3Y2M5YmRkNmU5ZGU1OTdiZjU4NmI2Yy5qcGeRkwXNAxTNAbyBoTAB.jpg', 'Nigerian Music Star Wizkid\nNigerian singer, Ayo Balogun who is popularly known as Wizkid has taken to social media to gush about his baby mama, Jada Pollock.\nThe singer who had a very successful outing at the WizkidFest, which held at the O2 arena, London over the weekend, toom to Twitter to wish Jada, the mother of his son, Zion, a happy birthday with so much love.\nRead Also: Wizkid Beats Me, Leaves Me With Bruises: 3rd Baby Mama, Jada Pollock Cries Out\nIt will be recalled that Pollock had in July this year, accused the Starboy via social media of abusing her physically and later claimed that her account was hacked.\nCelebrating the mother of his third child, he described her as a superwoman whom he got forever.\nHe wrote: Thank you, Jada! Thank you, Jada! Thank You, Jada!  Happy birthday! love you !!  superwoman!! My bad charge. Got you forever!!\n\nThank you Jada! Thank you Jada ! Thank You Jada! ?? Happy birthday!  love you !! ???????? superwoman!!  My bad charge. Got you forever !\n&mdash; Wizkid (@wizkidayo) October 21, 2019\n\n&nbsp;\nThe post Wizkid Gushes About 3rd Babymama, Jada Pollock appeared first on Information Nigeria.\n', 0, 'Mon, 21 Oct 2019 15:08:52 +0000'),
(457, 0, 'Shehu Sani Commends FG Over Order To Audit NDDC', 'Politics', 'https://www.informationng.com/2019/10/shehu-sani-commends-fg-over-order-to-audit-nddc.html', 'https://www.informationng.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/shehu-sani-reacts-to-buharis-appraisal-of-jonathan.jpg', 'Former lawmaker, Senator Shehu Sani has commended the Federal Government over the directive to audit the Niger Delta Development Commission (NDDC).\nSenator Shehu Sani\nRecall that some days ago, President Muhammadu Buhari ordered the audit of the commission over the non-implementation of projects.\nAlso Read: Shehu Sani Drums Support For Planned Labour Strike\nThe former lawmaker expressed that the decision is a right step considering the debts the nation is owing.\nSee his tweet below:\n\nWith trillions of Naira in debt,the audit of the NDDC as ordered by the FG is a step in the right direction and commendable.\n&mdash; Senator Shehu Sani (@ShehuSani) October 20, 2019\n\nThe post Shehu Sani Commends FG Over Order To Audit NDDC appeared first on Information Nigeria.\n', 0, 'Mon, 21 Oct 2019 15:06:00 +0000'),
(458, 0, 'Fuji Singer, Pasuma Pens Sweet Words To Mark Daughter’s Birthday', 'Entertainment', 'https://www.informationng.com/2019/10/fuji-singer-pasuma-pens-sweet-words-to-mark-daughters-birthday.html', 'https://alexis.lindaikejisblog.com/photos/shares/5ac673c04c29b.PNG', 'Fuji Singer Pasuma\nPopular Nigerian Fuji Icon, Pasuma has written sweet words of prayer to celebrate with his daughter who added another year to her age.\nTaking to his Instagram, he shared a photo of his daughter, Barakat Ajoke Oyindamola with words of prayer.\nIn his tweet, he prayed to God for her heart&#8217;s desire to be granted while he reminded her that he loves her and supports her.\nREAD ALSO &#8211; How Yinka Quadri, Liz Da Silva, Dayo Amusa, Pasuma stormed MC Oluomo’s daughter’s wedding introduction (photos)\nIn his own words: &#8220;HBD Barakat Ajoke Oyindamola,Blessing Child May God Almighty grant yhu yhur heart desires @oyin_cookie(Amin )Enjoy yhur cake day dear, daddy loves yhu &#8221;\nSee The Post Here:\nhttps://www.instagram.com/p/B34GgOGprhY/?utm_source=ig_web_copy_link\n&nbsp;\nThe post Fuji Singer, Pasuma Pens Sweet Words To Mark Daughter&#8217;s Birthday appeared first on Information Nigeria.\n', 0, 'Mon, 21 Oct 2019 15:03:38 +0000'),
(459, 0, 'Comedian Akpororo Flaunts New Car, Promotes New Song', 'Lifestyle', 'https://www.informationng.com/2019/10/comedian-akpororo-flaunts-new-car-promotes-new-song.html', 'http://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/Akpororo.png', 'Nigerian Comedian Akpororo\nPopular Nigerian Comedian Akpororo has shared a photo of himself with his new car on his Instagram.\nThe comedian who recently bought a car in celebration of his wife&#8217;s birthday has now bought one for himself.\nAttributing his success to God and his favour to his family, Akpororo shared the photo of his new car to his followers and fans alike.\nREAD ALSO &#8211; Nigerian Comedian Akpororo Surprises His Wife With Brand New SUV\nHe also used the medium to promote his latest single, &#8220;#Iserveaverybiggod&#8221; which is now available for download on all digital platforms.\nAccording to him: &#8220;Indeed I serve a very big God. All through the year, God has been good to me and my family. #iserveaverybiggod is my testimony of God’s grace and favor. This is my latest toy #iserveaverybiggod is ready for download on all digital platforms&#8230; get link on my bio #roroking #roronation.&#8221;\nSee His Post Here:\n\n  \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n View this post on Instagram\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n \n Indeed I serve a very big God. All through the year God has been good to me and my family. #iserveaverybiggod is my testimony of God’s grace and favor. This is my latest  toy #iserveaverybiggod is ready for download on all digital platforms&#8230; get link on my bio #roroking #roronation\nA post shared by  Jephthahakpororo@yahoo.com (@akpororo) on Oct 21, 2019 at 5:12am PDT\n\n\n\nThe post Comedian Akpororo Flaunts New Car, Promotes New Song appeared first on Information Nigeria.\n', 0, 'Mon, 21 Oct 2019 14:13:35 +0000'),
(460, 0, 'No Ministry Of Early Salary Payment In Gombe — Govt', 'Trending', 'https://www.informationng.com/2019/10/no-ministry-of-early-salary-payment-in-gombe-govt.html', 'https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Gombe.jpg', 'Gombe Ministry of Early Salary Payment\nThe government of Gombe state has reacted to a trending social media picture of a bus with the inscription: “Ministry of Early Salary Payment, Gombe state”.\n\n\n\n\n\nIsmaila Misilli, senior special assistant to the governor on media and publicity, said: “Our attention has been drawn to a photograph of a bus with a superimposed inscription of ‘ministry of early salary payment’ proudly belonging to Gombe state. ”\n“This is nothing but fake and reeks of desperados. Gombe state has no such ministry. Members of the public are warned to disregard the fake photo and desist from circulating it.\n“For the records, Gombe at the moment has 21 ministries sequel to executive order 1 issued by governor Muhammadu Inuwa Yahaya as follows:\nRead Also: Nigeria doesn&#8217;t need prayers; Gombe State Governor, Ibrahim Dankwambo\n\nMinistry of agriculture and husbandry\nMinistry of commerce, industry and tourism\nMinistry of education\nMinistry of higher education\nMinistry of finance and economic development\nMinistry of health\nMinistry of information and culture\nMinistry of justice\nMinistry of Lands and survey\nMinistry of local government and chieftaincy affairs\nMinistry of science, technology and innovation.\nMinistry of special duties\nMinistry of Works and transport\nMinistry of youths and sports development\nMinistry of women affairs and social development\nMinistry of water resources\nMinistry of rural, community development and cooperatives\nMinistry of internal security and ethical orientation\nMinistry of energy and mineral resources\nMinistry of environment and forest resources\nMinistry of housing and urban development.\n\n\n\n\n\n\nThe post No Ministry Of Early Salary Payment In Gombe — Govt appeared first on Information Nigeria.\n', 0, 'Mon, 21 Oct 2019 14:04:15 +0000'),
(461, 0, 'Woman Shares Details Of Lady In Pastor Wilson Viral Sex Video (Photo)', 'News', 'https://www.informationng.com/2019/10/woman-shares-details-of-lady-in-pastor-wilson-viral-sex-video-photo.html', 'https://www.informationng.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/10430814_img20191021125442882_jpeg3fb982eaa1a3439bca7022bcefa6ab6b.jpg', 'Pastor Wilson and Alleged Lady In Vidoe\nAn Internet user has shared a Facebook profile of the person she believes to be the lady in Pastor Wison&#8217;s Viral sex video.\nShe shared the profile and speculated that the lady was the recipient of the oral sex the Pastor was filmed having.\nREAD ALSO &#8211; ‘Lady In Pastor Wilson’s Sex Video Is The Daughter Of His Wife’s Best Friend&#8217;s – Pastor Thaddeus (Video)\nIn the video, Pastor David Wilson of the BibleWay Ministries &amp; World Out Reach, Inc., Texas, was clearly engrossed the act that he seems not aware he was being recorded.\nThe Internet user shared the profile whose name is &#8220;Corinthia Edwards.&#8221;\nApparently, Corinthia was promised a lead role by the pastor and when things didn&#8217;t go as planned, she leaked the video.\nSee Her Post Here:\n\n\nThe post Woman Shares Details Of Lady In Pastor Wilson Viral Sex Video (Photo) appeared first on Information Nigeria.\n', 0, 'Mon, 21 Oct 2019 13:59:43 +0000'),
(462, 0, 'Court Reduces Sowore’s Bail Condition To N50 Million', 'Metro News', 'https://www.informationng.com/2019/10/court-reduces-sowores-bail-condition-to-n50-million.html', 'https://www.informationng.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/5d91bcd112e1b.png', 'A Federal High Court in Abuja today heard Omoyele Sowore&#8217;s application for bail variation.\nFounder of Sahara Reporters Omoyele Sowore\nThe activist was arraigned on a four-count charge ranging from insulting President Muhammadu Buhari to money laundering.\nHe was granted bail condition of paying N150 million and had his movement restricted to Abuja.\nHowever, the activist&#8217;s camp had cried out that the bail conditions could not be met, with his lead counsel, Mr Femi Falana (SAN) describing the bails conditions as too stringent.\nAlso Read: 13th Headies: Falz Advocates For Sowore’s Release After Receiving Award (Video)\nAfter the hearing, Justice Ijeoma Ojukwu has now varied Omoyele Sowore and Olawale Bakare&#8217;s bail conditions.\nAccording to a report by SaharaReporters, Justice Ojukwu said she found it difficult to believe a man of Sowore&#8217;s pedigree did not have anyone to deposit N50 million.\nHence, Sowore bail condition was reviewed from N100 million to N50 million, and the 50 security deposits were also removed.\nThe post Court Reduces Sowore&#8217;s Bail Condition To N50 Million appeared first on Information Nigeria.\n', 0, 'Mon, 21 Oct 2019 13:56:10 +0000'),
(463, 0, 'Court To Resume Naira Marley’s Card Fraud Case Tomorrow', 'Metro News', 'https://www.informationng.com/2019/10/court-to-resume-naira-marleys-card-fraud-case-tomorrow.html', 'https://www.informationng.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/IMG_20190510_122029.jpg', 'Popular Nigerian rapper, Azeez Fashola, a.k.a. Naira Marley is set to resume trial at the Federal High Court in Lagos for his alleged internet fraud case.\n&#8216;Puta&#8217; Crooner, Naira Marley\n“The matter is coming up tomorrow,” Wilson Uwujaren, Economic and Financial Crimes Commission ((EFCC) spokesman, said when contacted by The Guardian on Monday.\nAlso Read: ‘Legwork Is Bigger Than Headies Award’ – Naira Marley\nRecall that in May, Justice Nicholas Onweibo adjourned the singer’s internet fraud case to October 22, 23 and 24 for accelerated hearing.\nHe was granted an N2 million bail, with two sureties in a like sum.\n*Sourced from The Guardian report\nThe post Court To Resume Naira Marley&#8217;s Card Fraud Case Tomorrow appeared first on Information Nigeria.\n', 0, 'Mon, 21 Oct 2019 13:51:14 +0000'),
(464, 0, 'Photos, Details Of Lady In Viral Video With Pastor Wilson Emerges Online', 'Trending', 'https://www.informationng.com/2019/10/photos-details-of-lady-in-viral-video-with-pastor-wilson-emerges-online.html', 'https://www.informationng.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Pastor-David-Wilson-R-Corinthia-edwards-M-and-his-wife.jpg', 'Photos and details of the lady allegedly in Pastor Wilson&#8217;s sex tape whom he was feasting on has emerged on the internet.\nPastor Wilson and Corinthia Edwards\nAccording to reports, the woman, Corinthia Edwards is said to be the daughter of the best-friend to the clergyman&#8217;s wife and a screenshot of her Facebook profile shows she lives in the city as the pastor.\nThe two were reportedly having an affair for a while and the pastor had allegedly given his words to make her a leader in the church choir but he failed to fulfil his promise.\nDuring one of their sexcapades, the lady filmed the video.\nEdwards, who was upset at the controversial clergyman, released the clip on the internet.\nTo make matters worse, the lady had also shared a photo of herself smiling with the words:\n“You’d be smiling like this too if Pastor Williams wrote the Lord’s Prayer in calligraphy on your south mouth with his tongue.”\nThe lady has since taken down all her social media accounts including Facebook and Instagram.\nRead Also: Chioma Shares A Glimpse Of Her Son Moving His Hands (Video)\nSee the post below:\n\nThe post Photos, Details Of Lady In Viral Video With Pastor Wilson Emerges Online appeared first on Information Nigeria.\n', 0, 'Mon, 21 Oct 2019 13:48:11 +0000'),
(465, 0, 'I’m Still A Virgin, Waiting For My Wedding Night: Bobrisky', 'Entertainment', 'https://www.informationng.com/2019/10/im-still-a-virgin-waiting-for-my-wedding-night-bobrisky.html', 'https://www.informationng.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/bobrisky-1-700x700-600x600.jpg', 'Popular male barbie and crossdresser, Bobrisky has revealed on his Instagram page that he is still a virgin.\nNigerian Cross-dresser Bobrisky\nThe popular crossdresser expressed that the weather is cold and he needed to cuddle up with to keep himself warn.\nAlso Read: Bobrisky Hangs Out With BBNaija Winner, Mercy (Video)\nHe, however, expressed that despite his desire, he is still a virgin waiting for his wedding night.\nSee his post below:\n\n  \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n View this post on Instagram\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n \n Everywhere is cold jeeeez&#8230;.. I need someone here but am still a virgin. Let me just wait till my wedding night\nA post shared by  okuneye idris (@bobrisky222) on Oct 21, 2019 at 3:13am PDT\n\n\n\nThe post I&#8217;m Still A Virgin, Waiting For My Wedding Night: Bobrisky appeared first on Information Nigeria.\n', 0, 'Mon, 21 Oct 2019 13:45:18 +0000'),
(466, 0, 'Inmates Of Kaduna ‘Torture Centre’ Were In Chains For 8years: Commissioner', 'Metro News', 'https://www.informationng.com/2019/10/inmates-of-kaduna-torture-centre-were-in-chains-for-8years-commissioner.html', 'https://www.informationng.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/mum-chains-daughter.jpg', 'Child chained to a pole\nHafsat Baba, Kaduna state commissioner for human services and social development, has revealed that the inmates of a religious rehabilitation centre in the state were held in chains for eight years.\nThe religious rehabilitation centre located at Kwanar Gurguwa in Igabi local government area of the state was raided on Saturday by police, setting free 147 inmates.\nAccording to the commissioner, the inmates were tortured and were in chains and a welder was contacted to remove the chains from their legs.\nRead Also: Horrifying Chronicles Of Police Extortion, Harassment, Torture Of Harmless Citizens\n“They have been under torture. They were all in chains. We have to call a welder to remove the chains in their legs. Some of them have been in chains for eight years. They just removed the chains this afternoon,” she said.\nThe post Inmates Of Kaduna &#8216;Torture Centre&#8217; Were In Chains For 8years: Commissioner appeared first on Information Nigeria.\n', 0, 'Mon, 21 Oct 2019 13:44:07 +0000'),
(467, 0, 'Mr President, Where Is Your Humanity? Cleric Slams Buhari Over Abducted Leah Sharibu', 'News', 'https://www.informationng.com/2019/10/mr-president-where-is-your-humanity-cleric-slams-buhari-over-abducted-leah-sharibu.html', 'https://www.informationng.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Leahh.jpg', 'Leah Sharibu\nA cleric in Jos, Plateau State, Gideon Para-Mallam, has said that President Muhammadu Buhari is yet to reach out to Nathan Sharibu, Leah’s father.\nLeah was one of the more than 100 female students of Government Girls Science and Technical Secondary School, Dapchi, kidnapped by a faction of Boko Haram in February 2018, but was held back in captivity because of her faith.\nIn a statement issued on his birthday, Para-Mallam said the president was yet to call Sharibu to give him updates on efforts at rescuing his daughter.\n“On October 15, Leah’s father, Nathan Sharibu and I were on the phone again. We connect regularly and this has been the case since March 2018, till date,” he said.\n“He said he had not heard a single word about his daughter’s release beyond the promises. He also confirmed that he had not received any phone calls or updates from the President of this country.\nRead Also: Leah Sharibu: We Will Not Pay Ransom For Any Boko Haram Captive — Presidency\n“Why is this the case? I am wondering deeply. Mr President, where is your humanity? Is life all about enjoying power in Aso Rock? You are a father and Nathan Sharibu is also a father. Before you were anything in government, you were a father.\n“Mr President, 603 days? Would you have the peace of mind to lead Nigeria? A few minutes into writing this statement, Leah’s father and I were on the phone again. He shared with me that their life as a family is one of daily agony and pain, but they remain thankful to God.\n“I encouraged him once again as I normally do, to remain hopeful about Leah’s release. He went further to tell me that October 14 was rather a very difficult night for him because he dreamt about Leah. He seemed distressed and unhappy.”\nThe post Mr President, Where Is Your Humanity? Cleric Slams Buhari Over Abducted Leah Sharibu appeared first on Information Nigeria.\n', 0, 'Mon, 21 Oct 2019 13:36:27 +0000'),
(468, 0, 'Nnamdi Kanu’s Mother Died From Shock Of Military Invasion — IPOB', 'Trending', 'https://www.informationng.com/2019/10/nnamdi-kanus-mother-died-from-shock-of-military-invasion-ipob.html', 'https://www.informationng.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/Nnamdi-Kanu-653x365.png', '&nbsp;\nIPOB Leader, Nnamdi Kanu\nThe Indigenous People of Biafra, IPOB, has said the mother of its Leader, Mazi Nnamdi Kanu, Ugoeze Sally Kanu, died from the shock of the 2017 military invasion of her home in Afaraukwu, Umuahia, Abia state.\nDuring the weekend, Kanu had in a short video confirmed that his mother died at a German hospital on the 30th of August, 2019 after battling with illness.\nIn a statement by IPOB Media and Publicity Secretary, Emma Powerful, the group said Kanu&#8217;s mother died from ‘extreme shock from military invasion of her home under the guise of Operation Python Dance.\n“We the global family of IPOB felt pain and sorrow for the announcement of the sudden death of our mother, Ugoeze Sally Kanu who died on 30th of August, 2019 in a German hospital after a brief illness because of numerous attacks by security forces on her Afaraukwu family and the people of Biafra since 2015.\n“ She died of heart failure as a result of the incessant military attacks on her home. The trauma of the very brutal Operation Python Dance military invasion was the tipping point. As a peace-loving and deeply compassionate mother, she never recovered from the shock of seeing 28 able-bodied young men lying dead inside her compound following that invasion.\n“Our heartfelt condolences to the entire IPOB family worldwide but more specifically to our indomitable leader, Mazi Nnamdi Kanu and his entire family of His Royal Majesty Sir Eze I. O. Kanu, on the passing on to glory of the mother of all mothers, late Ugoeze Sally Okwu-Kanu, the womb that gave birth to the most bravest of all, the sagacious, the indefatigable and the unstoppable enigmatic Leader of IPOB worldwide, Mazi Nnamdi Kanu. IPOB worldwide commiserate with our leader Mazi Nnamdi Kanu and entire family for the irreparable loss and vacuum created by enemy within the family of Biafra.\nRead Also: Onitsha Inferno A Terrorist Attack To Wipe Out Biafran: IPOB\n“We pray to Almighty God Chukwu Okike Abiama to grant us the fortitude to bear the loss. Nne Ugoeze, you are no more physically here with us but your spirit lives on. The struggle that you led with your family members cannot be in vain and we assure you that Biafra independence must come. This is to prove to you that we shall not stop nor grow weary until Biafra freedom is totally restored on your behalf and in your honour and that of many others who lost their lives for us to live.\n“The precious family of Eze Okwu Kanu and Biafran families you left behind, we lift them to the Highest God Chukwu Okike Abiama in prayers for total and continued divine favour and protection until freedom is totally celebrated in our lifetime.”\nThe post Nnamdi Kanu&#8217;s Mother Died From Shock Of Military Invasion — IPOB appeared first on Information Nigeria.\n', 0, 'Mon, 21 Oct 2019 13:34:34 +0000'),
(469, 0, 'Prince Harry Speaks About Tension With His Brother, William', 'Lifestyle', 'https://www.informationng.com/2019/10/prince-harry-speaks-about-tension-with-his-brother-william.html', 'https://www.informationng.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/5dad3c987e197.png', 'Prince William, Prince Harry\nPrince Harry for the first time has admitted that he and William are traveling on &#8216;different paths&#8217;.\nIn a candid interview, the Duke of Sussex confirmed that there has been deepening tensions between himself and William. This is coming after months of speculation that there is a strain in the brothers’ relationship.\nRead Also: I will be fine if my children were gay- Prince William says as he visits LGBTQ charity\nHarry made this known in a  TV documentary broadcast this weekend adding that he will not allow the press to bully him and his wife Meghan Markle. &#8216;I will not be bullied into playing a game that killed my mum.&#8217;  \nOn if the rift with his brother was true, Harry pointedly refused to deny a falling out the added;\n‘Part of this role, part of this job and this family being under the pressure it is under, inevitably stuff happens. But look, we are brothers, we will always be brothers. We are certainly on different paths at the moment but I will always be there for him and, as I know, he will always be there for me.’\n‘We don’t see as much as we used to because we are so busy but I love him dearly and the majority of stuff is created out of nothing. As brothers, you have good days, you have bad days.’\nHarry’s comments came during an interview with ITV presenter Tom Bradby &#8211; a long-time friend of the prince. Bradby’s hour-long documentary, titled ‘Harry &amp; Meghan: An African Journey’, followed the royal couple during their official tour of Africa last month.\nOn how he deals with the pressures of his life, Harry said it is a matter of &#8216;constant management&#8217;, adding: &#8216;I thought I was out of the woods and then suddenly it all came back, and this is something that I have to manage.\n&#8216;Part of this job, and part of any job, like everybody, is putting on a brave face and turning a cheek to a lot of the stuff, but again, for me and again for my wife, of course there is a lot of stuff that hurts, especially when the majority of it is untrue.\n&#8216;But all we need to do is focus on being real, and focus on being the people that we are, and standing up for what we believe in.\n&#8216;I will not be bullied into playing a game that killed my mum.&#8217;\nThe post Prince Harry Speaks About Tension With His Brother, William appeared first on Information Nigeria.\n', 0, 'Mon, 21 Oct 2019 12:41:18 +0000'),
(470, 0, '‘Dead Ex-Wife’ Visits Man On Day Of His New Wedding', 'Metro News', 'https://www.informationng.com/2019/10/dead-ex-wife-visits-man-on-day-of-his-new-wedding.html', 'https://www.gistreel.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/5dacd2f8ab8fa.png', 'A Twitter user identified as olamipos_tabiti has recounted how her cousin found out that her husband-to-be is married.\nAccording to her, the man had told her cousin that his wife was dead but refused taking down her photos in his house.\nHowever, the woman whose husband claimed was dead, showed up at the wedding with proof of their marriage.\nIn her tweet, she had said: &#8220;My cousin is getting married today or should I say supposed to get married today, and a Lady showed up in her house as the husband’s housewife, of which the man told her his wife is late, True life story&#8221;\nREAD ALSO &#8211; TVC Host Breaks Down In Tears, Apologizes To Her Husband Live On TV Over &#8216;Child Abuse&#8217; Comments (Video)\nSee Post Here:\nOlamipo&#8217;s Tweet\nOlamipo&#8217;s Tweet\nThe post &#8216;Dead Ex-Wife&#8217; Visits Man On Day Of His New Wedding appeared first on Information Nigeria.\n', 0, 'Mon, 21 Oct 2019 12:41:05 +0000'),
(471, 0, 'Chioma Shares A Glimpse Of Her Son Moving His Hands (Video)', 'Entertainment', 'https://www.informationng.com/2019/10/chioma-shares-a-glimpse-of-her-son-moving-his-hands-video.html', 'https://www.informationng.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Davido-Chioma2.jpg', 'Davido&#8217;s third babymama and fiancee, Chioma Avirl Rowland alias Chefchi shared a glimpse of their son, Ifeanyi David Jr moving his tiny precious fingers.\nDavido and Chioma\nChioma captioned the video:\n&#8220;In love&#8221;\nThe new mom had earlier shared a video of herself after childbirth laying beside her husband-to-be, who was fast asleep, on the hospital bed.\nThe chef praised Davido for being around to witness the whole childbirth experience.\nInformation Nigeria recalls the singer had revealed that he was in the labor room after a fan asked him about his upcoming album.\n\nI Dey delivery room brother ! Make we talk this matter after  https://t.co/vzBKgrUmDe\n&mdash; Davido (@iam_Davido) October 19, 2019\n\nRead Also: “G-String Is Not For All Ladies”, Says Actress Ekwutousi As She Pulls Off Her Pant (Video)\nWatch the video below:\n\nhttps://www.informationng.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/75408257_2940173716017715_5379700574060488288_n.mp4\nThe post Chioma Shares A Glimpse Of Her Son Moving His Hands (Video) appeared first on Information Nigeria.\n', 0, 'Mon, 21 Oct 2019 12:27:30 +0000'),
(472, 0, '‘Daddy Of The Year’- Chioma Appreciates Husband, Davido', 'News', 'https://www.informationng.com/2019/10/daddy-of-the-year-chioma-appreciates-husband-davido.html', 'https://www.informationng.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Davido-and-Chioma-9jahotstars.jpeg', 'Afro Music Star Davido and Chioma\nDavido’s fiancé, Chioma took to her Instagram to appreciate her husband for coming through for her.\nTaking to her Instagram story, she praised Davido for staying by her side throughout the moment she gave birth to her baby boy and in the labour room.\nREAD ALSO &#8211; “I Am In The Delivery Room” &#8211; Davido Reveals Chioma Is About To Give Birth\nChioma and Davido will be married in 2020 as plans have already begun for their marriage.\nThey have also welcomed a child which has left fans very happy for the couple.\nIn Chioma&#8217;s Instagram story, she wrote: “Daddy of the year.”\nSee Photo Here:\nChioma&#8217;s Instagram Story\n&nbsp;\nThe post &#8216;Daddy Of The Year&#8217;- Chioma Appreciates Husband, Davido appeared first on Information Nigeria.\n', 0, 'Mon, 21 Oct 2019 12:18:00 +0000'),
(473, 0, 'Breaking: Court Orders Forfeiture Of Saraki’s Properties In Lagos', 'News', 'https://www.informationng.com/2019/10/breaking-court-orders-forfeiture-of-two-of-sarakis-properties-in-lagos.html', 'https://www.informationng.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/saraki.jpg', 'Bukola Saraki\nA federal high court sitting in Lagos has ordered the temporary forfeiture of two properties belonging to Bukola Saraki, senate president of the 8th National Assembly at Ikoyi Lagos state.\nThis was after a counsel of the Economic and Financial Crimes Commission ( EFCC), Nnaemeka Omewa approached the court, seeking an order of interim forfeiture of the properties located at 17A McDonald Road, Ikoyi, Eti Osa local government area of Lagos.\nHe had told the court that they were acquired through “proceeds of unlawful activities”.\nRead Also: Why Saraki Blocked Confirmation Of EFCC Chairman, Magu: Alaafin Of Oyo\nSome other reliefs the EFCC sought  included, “an order of this honourable Court forfeiting to the Federal Government of Nigeria landed property with appurtenances situate, lying and known as No. 17A McDonald Road, Ikoyi, Eti Osa Local Government Area of Lagos State found and recovered from the respondent which property is reasonably suspected to have been acquired with proceeds of unlawful activity”.\nThe post Breaking: Court Orders Forfeiture Of Saraki&#8217;s Properties In Lagos appeared first on Information Nigeria.\n', 0, 'Mon, 21 Oct 2019 15:33:15 +0000'),
(474, 0, 'Glory Osei, Muyiwa Folorunsho Of LandLagos Attacked For Allegedly Defrauding Employees', 'Gossip', 'https://www.informationng.com/2019/10/glory-osei-muyiwa-folorunsho-of-landlagos-attacked-for-allegedly-defrauding-employees.html', 'https://www.informationng.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/10431260_gloryoseiandmuyiwafolorunsho_pngf88e4eef2bb70be82d7736b56f6e55a6-1.png', 'Popular entrepreneurs, Muyiwa Folorunsho and Glory Osei, have been accused of fraud and maltreatment of staff by their former employees.\nGlory Osei and Muyiwa Folorunsho\nThe twitter user also alleged that the two entrepreneurs are married couple.\nAlso Read: Glory Osei Reacts To Former Employee’s Fraud Allegations\nTwitter is currently buzzing as a former employee of the duo accuses them of fraud, toxic work environment, deducting from their salaries or sacking them over trivial mistakes and more.\nSee post below:\n\n&#8211; Lady calls out a job owner , Glory Osei ,and her husband, Muyiwa ,for alleged scam and maltreatment of staff and partners. pic.twitter.com/WOG3EoSNCA\n&mdash; SubDeliveryZone (@SubDeliveryZone) October 21, 2019\n\n&nbsp;\nThe post Glory Osei, Muyiwa Folorunsho Of LandLagos Attacked For Allegedly Defrauding Employees appeared first on Information Nigeria.\n', 0, 'Mon, 21 Oct 2019 15:32:48 +0000'),
(475, 0, 'Abuja Court Softens Sowore’s Bail Conditions', 'News', 'https://www.informationng.com/2019/10/abuja-court-softens-sowores-bail-conditions.html', 'https://www.informationng.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/sowore-777x437.jpg', 'Omoyele Sowore\nA Federal High Court in Abuja has reduced the bail conditions on the convener of #RevolutionNow, Omoyele Sowore and his co-defendant, Olawale Bakare over charges of treason.\nThe condition was reduced by Justice Ijeoma Ojukwu on Monday. She reduced Sowore’s bail bond to the N50m down from N100m, while Bakare’s bail was reduced from N50m to N20m.\nRead Also: 13th Headies: Falz Advocates For Sowore&#8217;s Release After Receiving Award (Video)\nOjukwu also ordered that sureties to the defendants are no longer expected to deposit evidence of the funds with the court registrar.\nThe post Abuja Court Softens Sowore&#8217;s Bail Conditions appeared first on Information Nigeria.\n', 0, 'Mon, 21 Oct 2019 15:31:29 +0000'),
(476, 0, 'Davido’s Son Models For Mario And Juliet As Brand Ambassador', 'Entertainment', 'https://www.informationng.com/2019/10/davidos-son-models-for-mario-and-juliet-as-brand-ambassador.html', 'https://www.informationng.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Davidos-new-baby.png', 'Adedeji Ifeanyi Adeleke, Davido’s newborn baby boy has been announced brand ambassador to Mario and Juliet Diapers.\nDavido welcomes baby boy\nThe artist and Chioma’s son, David Adedeji Ifeanyi Adeleke got a planned endorsement with baby products brand, Mario and Juliet a month before he was born.\nAlso Read: Chioma Shares A Glimpse Of Her Son Moving His Hands (Video)\nFew hours after the baby&#8217;s arrival was announced, the company revealed him as a Brand Ambassador.\nSee post below:\nDavido and son\n&nbsp;\nThe post Davido’s Son Models For Mario And Juliet As Brand Ambassador appeared first on Information Nigeria.\n', 0, 'Mon, 21 Oct 2019 15:29:12 +0000'),
(477, 0, 'Yoruba Is Derived From ‘Yariba’ And It Means ‘Shady, Unreliable’: Fani-Kayode', 'Trending', 'https://www.informationng.com/2019/10/yoruba-is-derived-from-yariba-and-it-means-shady-unreliable-fani-kayode.html', 'https://www.informationng.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/ffk.jpg', 'Femi Fani Kayode\nA former minister of aviation, Femi Fani-Kayode has said that the name &#8220;Yoruba&#8221; is derived from &#8220;Yariba&#8221; and it means &#8220;shady and unreliable&#8221;.\nAccording to Fani-Kayode, &#8216;Yariba&#8217; is the name given to the Southwest(SW) by the Fulani. He added that while the Southeast rejected the name &#8216;Yamiri&#8217; given to them by the Fulani, the Southwest accepted theirs.\nHe said in a few tweets on Monday thus:\nTwo names that the Fulani gave to southerners: &#8220;Yamiri&#8221;, in reference to SE and &#8220;Yariba&#8221; in reference to SW. The SE rejected that name but the SW accepted it. The name &#8220;Yoruba&#8221; derives from &#8220;Yariba&#8221; and it means &#8220;shady and unreliable&#8221;. I reject that strange name and label.\nI am not a &#8220;Yariba&#8221; or &#8220;Yoruba&#8221; but an &#8220;Omo Karo Jire&#8221; or an &#8220;Oduduwan&#8221; and my language are not &#8220;Yoruba&#8221; but &#8220;Anago&#8221;. We are what we call ourselves. We are not &#8220;shady and unreliable&#8221;(Yariba) and we must not accept names that are given to us by our historical adversaries&#8230;\n&#8230;Any Omo Karo Jire or Oduduwan that continues to call himself a &#8220;Yoruba&#8221; is lost and does not know the implications of what he is doing to his own people. He is simply affirming and confirming an insulting label that has deep sinister, mystical and spiritual connotations&#8230;\nRead Also:Igbo Women Were Placed On Earth For Yoruba Men: Ycee\n&#8230;The word &#8220;Yoruba&#8221; did not even exist until the 18th century and even then most of the tribes of the SW, including the Oyo&#8217;s, rejected it due to its origin and meaning. The word &#8220;Yoruba&#8221; is alien to our culture and not known in the Anago language. Oduduwans please take note.\n\n&#8230;.I am not a &quot;Yariba&quot; or &quot;Yoruba&quot; but an &quot;Omo Karo Jire&quot; or an &quot;Oduduwan&quot; and my lanuage is not &quot;Yoruba&quot; but &quot;Anago&quot;. We are what we call ourselves. We are not &quot;shady and uneliable&quot;(Yariba) and we must not accept names that are given to us by our historical adversaries&#8230;\n&mdash; Femi Fani-Kayode (@realFFK) October 21, 2019\n\n\n&#8230;The word &quot;Yoruba&quot; did not even exist until the 18th century and even then most of the tribes of the SW, including the Oyo&#39;s, rejected it due to its origin and meaning. The word &quot;Yoruba&quot; is alien to our culture and not known in the Anago language. Oduduwans please take note.\n&mdash; Femi Fani-Kayode (@realFFK) October 21, 2019\n\nThe post Yoruba Is Derived From &#8216;Yariba&#8217; And It Means &#8216;Shady, Unreliable&#8217;: Fani-Kayode appeared first on Information Nigeria.\n', 0, 'Mon, 21 Oct 2019 15:18:23 +0000'),
(478, 0, 'Strange Moments Two Cats Disappear At Aba Market [Video]', 'Metro News', 'https://www.informationng.com/2019/10/strange-moments-two-cats-disappear-at-aba-market-video.html', 'https://www.informationng.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/cat.jpg', 'Cat\nA CCTV footage has shown the mysterious moment two cats disappeared at a market in Aba, Abia state.\nIn the video shared via Twitter, two cats were seen strolling through an empty corridor of shops, when they suddenly disappeared at the same time.\nHowever, some social media users have argued that the video might have been tampered with, while some are of the firm belief that the cat really disappears.\nRead Also: Brides Catches Groom Sexually Assaulting Her Bridesmaid; Goes Ahead To Marry Him\nSee video below\n\n&#8211; CCTV captures the moment two cats disappeared at a market in Aba ,Abia state. pic.twitter.com/InUeGnQi4v\n&mdash; SubDeliveryZone (@SubDeliveryZone) October 21, 2019\n\nThe post Strange Moments Two Cats Disappear At Aba Market [Video] appeared first on Information Nigeria.\n', 0, 'Mon, 21 Oct 2019 15:16:48 +0000'),
(479, 0, 'Mungo Park Didn’t Discover Source Of River Niger, Stop The Brainwash: Reno Omokri', 'Education', 'https://www.informationng.com/2019/10/mungo-park-didnt-discover-source-of-river-niger-stop-the-brainwash-reno-omokri.html', 'https://www.informationng.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Reno-book-signing-700x466.jpg', 'Popular social media activist, Reno Omokri has queried the decision of curicculum makers over the teaching that Mungo Park discovered the source of River Niger.\nNigerian author, Reno Omokri\nAccording to the activist, the common saying that Mungo Park discovered the source of River Niger is a historical lie.\nAlso Read: Reno Omokri Helps Victim Of Onitsha Fire Outbreak (Video)\nHe went further to express that the continuous teaching of that knowledge in school is a deliberate attempt to brainwash Nigerians.\nSee his post below:\n\nWhy does Nigeria still allow that colonial historical lie that Mungo Park discovered the source of the River Niger to be taught in schools? How can Nigeria continue to brainwash her own children with a colonial lie?\n                  #TableShaker#FreeLeahSharibu #RenosNuggets\n&mdash; Reno Omokri (@renoomokri) October 21, 2019\n\nThe post Mungo Park Didn&#8217;t Discover Source Of River Niger, Stop The Brainwash: Reno Omokri appeared first on Information Nigeria.\n', 0, 'Mon, 21 Oct 2019 15:13:41 +0000'),
(480, 0, 'Prophet Jailed For Stealing Member’s International Passport', 'Metro News', 'https://www.informationng.com/2019/10/prophet-jailed-for-stealing-members-international-passport.html', 'https://www.informationng.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/court-jails-woman-for-exposing-her-cheating-boss-who-was-having-affair-with-a-colleague.jpg', '\nA Prophet in Zimbabwe has been sentenced to 6 months in prison after he stole the passport of a member of his congregation and used it to travel to South Africa under the falsehood that he was praying for it.\nThe prophet identified as Shepherd Mbili was convicted by a Bulawayo Magistrate, Zimbabwe after he pleaded guilty to the charges levelled against him.\nRead Also: Photos, Details Of Lady In Viral Video With Pastor Wilson Emerges Online\nThe prophet was said to have asked Mr Godknows to bring his passport and academic certificates for anointing, he then prayed for it and advised the complainant not to open the envelope fully knowing that he had stolen his passport.\n“He told me not to open the envelope until I’m ready to use it On the 6th of October I opened the envelope to check the last date I went to Zambia and I found out that my passport was missing. I went to look for Prophet Mbili and his wife told me that he had travelled to South Africa with my passport and would be back soon” said the congregant whose passport was stolen.\nThe post Prophet Jailed For Stealing Member&#8217;s International Passport appeared first on Information Nigeria.\n', 0, 'Mon, 21 Oct 2019 15:11:58 +0000'),
(481, 0, 'Wizkid Gushes About 3rd Babymama, Jada Pollock', 'Entertainment', 'https://www.informationng.com/2019/10/wizkid-gushes-about-3rd-babymama-jada-pollock.html', 'https://www.informationng.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/b7Zk9kpTURBXy9lZjY3ZWIxMDc3Y2M5YmRkNmU5ZGU1OTdiZjU4NmI2Yy5qcGeRkwXNAxTNAbyBoTAB.jpg', 'Nigerian Music Star Wizkid\nNigerian singer, Ayo Balogun who is popularly known as Wizkid has taken to social media to gush about his baby mama, Jada Pollock.\nThe singer who had a very successful outing at the WizkidFest, which held at the O2 arena, London over the weekend, toom to Twitter to wish Jada, the mother of his son, Zion, a happy birthday with so much love.\nRead Also: Wizkid Beats Me, Leaves Me With Bruises: 3rd Baby Mama, Jada Pollock Cries Out\nIt will be recalled that Pollock had in July this year, accused the Starboy via social media of abusing her physically and later claimed that her account was hacked.\nCelebrating the mother of his third child, he described her as a superwoman whom he got forever.\nHe wrote: Thank you, Jada! Thank you, Jada! Thank You, Jada!  Happy birthday! love you !!  superwoman!! My bad charge. Got you forever!!\n\nThank you Jada! Thank you Jada ! Thank You Jada! ?? Happy birthday!  love you !! ???????? superwoman!!  My bad charge. Got you forever !\n&mdash; Wizkid (@wizkidayo) October 21, 2019\n\n&nbsp;\nThe post Wizkid Gushes About 3rd Babymama, Jada Pollock appeared first on Information Nigeria.\n', 0, 'Mon, 21 Oct 2019 15:08:52 +0000'),
(482, 0, 'Shehu Sani Commends FG Over Order To Audit NDDC', 'Politics', 'https://www.informationng.com/2019/10/shehu-sani-commends-fg-over-order-to-audit-nddc.html', 'https://www.informationng.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/shehu-sani-reacts-to-buharis-appraisal-of-jonathan.jpg', 'Former lawmaker, Senator Shehu Sani has commended the Federal Government over the directive to audit the Niger Delta Development Commission (NDDC).\nSenator Shehu Sani\nRecall that some days ago, President Muhammadu Buhari ordered the audit of the commission over the non-implementation of projects.\nAlso Read: Shehu Sani Drums Support For Planned Labour Strike\nThe former lawmaker expressed that the decision is a right step considering the debts the nation is owing.\nSee his tweet below:\n\nWith trillions of Naira in debt,the audit of the NDDC as ordered by the FG is a step in the right direction and commendable.\n&mdash; Senator Shehu Sani (@ShehuSani) October 20, 2019\n\nThe post Shehu Sani Commends FG Over Order To Audit NDDC appeared first on Information Nigeria.\n', 0, 'Mon, 21 Oct 2019 15:06:00 +0000'),
