(734, 0, 'Yoruba Is Derived From ‘Yariba’ And It Means ‘Shady, Unreliable’: Fani-Kayode', 'Trending', 'https://www.informationng.com/2019/10/yoruba-is-derived-from-yariba-and-it-means-shady-unreliable-fani-kayode.html', 'https://www.informationng.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/ffk.jpg', 'Femi Fani Kayode\nA former minister of aviation, Femi Fani-Kayode has said that the name &#8220;Yoruba&#8221; is derived from &#8220;Yariba&#8221; and it means &#8220;shady and unreliable&#8221;.\nAccording to Fani-Kayode, &#8216;Yariba&#8217; is the name given to the Southwest(SW) by the Fulani. He added that while the Southeast rejected the name &#8216;Yamiri&#8217; given to them by the Fulani, the Southwest accepted theirs.\nHe said in a few tweets on Monday thus:\nTwo names that the Fulani gave to southerners: &#8220;Yamiri&#8221;, in reference to SE and &#8220;Yariba&#8221; in reference to SW. The SE rejected that name but the SW accepted it. The name &#8220;Yoruba&#8221; derives from &#8220;Yariba&#8221; and it means &#8220;shady and unreliable&#8221;. I reject that strange name and label.\nI am not a &#8220;Yariba&#8221; or &#8220;Yoruba&#8221; but an &#8220;Omo Karo Jire&#8221; or an &#8220;Oduduwan&#8221; and my language are not &#8220;Yoruba&#8221; but &#8220;Anago&#8221;. We are what we call ourselves. We are not &#8220;shady and unreliable&#8221;(Yariba) and we must not accept names that are given to us by our historical adversaries&#8230;\n&#8230;Any Omo Karo Jire or Oduduwan that continues to call himself a &#8220;Yoruba&#8221; is lost and does not know the implications of what he is doing to his own people. He is simply affirming and confirming an insulting label that has deep sinister, mystical and spiritual connotations&#8230;\nRead Also:Igbo Women Were Placed On Earth For Yoruba Men: Ycee\n&#8230;The word &#8220;Yoruba&#8221; did not even exist until the 18th century and even then most of the tribes of the SW, including the Oyo&#8217;s, rejected it due to its origin and meaning. The word &#8220;Yoruba&#8221; is alien to our culture and not known in the Anago language. Oduduwans please take note.\n\n&#8230;.I am not a &quot;Yariba&quot; or &quot;Yoruba&quot; but an &quot;Omo Karo Jire&quot; or an &quot;Oduduwan&quot; and my lanuage is not &quot;Yoruba&quot; but &quot;Anago&quot;. We are what we call ourselves. We are not &quot;shady and uneliable&quot;(Yariba) and we must not accept names that are given to us by our historical adversaries&#8230;\n&mdash; Femi Fani-Kayode (@realFFK) October 21, 2019\n\n\n&#8230;The word &quot;Yoruba&quot; did not even exist until the 18th century and even then most of the tribes of the SW, including the Oyo&#39;s, rejected it due to its origin and meaning. The word &quot;Yoruba&quot; is alien to our culture and not known in the Anago language. Oduduwans please take note.\n&mdash; Femi Fani-Kayode (@realFFK) October 21, 2019\n\nThe post Yoruba Is Derived From &#8216;Yariba&#8217; And It Means &#8216;Shady, Unreliable&#8217;: Fani-Kayode appeared first on Information Nigeria.\n', 0, 'Mon, 21 Oct 2019 15:18:23 +0000'),
(735, 0, 'Strange Moments Two Cats Disappear At Aba Market [Video]', 'Metro News', 'https://www.informationng.com/2019/10/strange-moments-two-cats-disappear-at-aba-market-video.html', 'https://www.informationng.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/cat.jpg', 'Cat\nA CCTV footage has shown the mysterious moment two cats disappeared at a market in Aba, Abia state.\nIn the video shared via Twitter, two cats were seen strolling through an empty corridor of shops, when they suddenly disappeared at the same time.\nHowever, some social media users have argued that the video might have been tampered with, while some are of the firm belief that the cat really disappears.\nRead Also: Brides Catches Groom Sexually Assaulting Her Bridesmaid; Goes Ahead To Marry Him\nSee video below\n\n&#8211; CCTV captures the moment two cats disappeared at a market in Aba ,Abia state. pic.twitter.com/InUeGnQi4v\n&mdash; SubDeliveryZone (@SubDeliveryZone) October 21, 2019\n\nThe post Strange Moments Two Cats Disappear At Aba Market [Video] appeared first on Information Nigeria.\n', 0, 'Mon, 21 Oct 2019 15:16:48 +0000'),
(736, 0, 'Mungo Park Didn’t Discover Source Of River Niger, Stop The Brainwash: Reno Omokri', 'Education', 'https://www.informationng.com/2019/10/mungo-park-didnt-discover-source-of-river-niger-stop-the-brainwash-reno-omokri.html', 'https://www.informationng.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Reno-book-signing-700x466.jpg', 'Popular social media activist, Reno Omokri has queried the decision of curicculum makers over the teaching that Mungo Park discovered the source of River Niger.\nNigerian author, Reno Omokri\nAccording to the activist, the common saying that Mungo Park discovered the source of River Niger is a historical lie.\nAlso Read: Reno Omokri Helps Victim Of Onitsha Fire Outbreak (Video)\nHe went further to express that the continuous teaching of that knowledge in school is a deliberate attempt to brainwash Nigerians.\nSee his post below:\n\nWhy does Nigeria still allow that colonial historical lie that Mungo Park discovered the source of the River Niger to be taught in schools? How can Nigeria continue to brainwash her own children with a colonial lie?\n                  #TableShaker#FreeLeahSharibu #RenosNuggets\n&mdash; Reno Omokri (@renoomokri) October 21, 2019\n\nThe post Mungo Park Didn&#8217;t Discover Source Of River Niger, Stop The Brainwash: Reno Omokri appeared first on Information Nigeria.\n', 0, 'Mon, 21 Oct 2019 15:13:41 +0000'),
(737, 0, 'Prophet Jailed For Stealing Member’s International Passport', 'Metro News', 'https://www.informationng.com/2019/10/prophet-jailed-for-stealing-members-international-passport.html', 'https://www.informationng.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/court-jails-woman-for-exposing-her-cheating-boss-who-was-having-affair-with-a-colleague.jpg', '\nA Prophet in Zimbabwe has been sentenced to 6 months in prison after he stole the passport of a member of his congregation and used it to travel to South Africa under the falsehood that he was praying for it.\nThe prophet identified as Shepherd Mbili was convicted by a Bulawayo Magistrate, Zimbabwe after he pleaded guilty to the charges levelled against him.\nRead Also: Photos, Details Of Lady In Viral Video With Pastor Wilson Emerges Online\nThe prophet was said to have asked Mr Godknows to bring his passport and academic certificates for anointing, he then prayed for it and advised the complainant not to open the envelope fully knowing that he had stolen his passport.\n“He told me not to open the envelope until I’m ready to use it On the 6th of October I opened the envelope to check the last date I went to Zambia and I found out that my passport was missing. I went to look for Prophet Mbili and his wife told me that he had travelled to South Africa with my passport and would be back soon” said the congregant whose passport was stolen.\nThe post Prophet Jailed For Stealing Member&#8217;s International Passport appeared first on Information Nigeria.\n', 0, 'Mon, 21 Oct 2019 15:11:58 +0000'),
(738, 0, 'Wizkid Gushes About 3rd Babymama, Jada Pollock', 'Entertainment', 'https://www.informationng.com/2019/10/wizkid-gushes-about-3rd-babymama-jada-pollock.html', 'https://www.informationng.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/b7Zk9kpTURBXy9lZjY3ZWIxMDc3Y2M5YmRkNmU5ZGU1OTdiZjU4NmI2Yy5qcGeRkwXNAxTNAbyBoTAB.jpg', 'Nigerian Music Star Wizkid\nNigerian singer, Ayo Balogun who is popularly known as Wizkid has taken to social media to gush about his baby mama, Jada Pollock.\nThe singer who had a very successful outing at the WizkidFest, which held at the O2 arena, London over the weekend, toom to Twitter to wish Jada, the mother of his son, Zion, a happy birthday with so much love.\nRead Also: Wizkid Beats Me, Leaves Me With Bruises: 3rd Baby Mama, Jada Pollock Cries Out\nIt will be recalled that Pollock had in July this year, accused the Starboy via social media of abusing her physically and later claimed that her account was hacked.\nCelebrating the mother of his third child, he described her as a superwoman whom he got forever.\nHe wrote: Thank you, Jada! Thank you, Jada! Thank You, Jada!  Happy birthday! love you !!  superwoman!! My bad charge. Got you forever!!\n\nThank you Jada! Thank you Jada ! Thank You Jada! ?? Happy birthday!  love you !! ???????? superwoman!!  My bad charge. Got you forever !\n&mdash; Wizkid (@wizkidayo) October 21, 2019\n\n&nbsp;\nThe post Wizkid Gushes About 3rd Babymama, Jada Pollock appeared first on Information Nigeria.\n', 0, 'Mon, 21 Oct 2019 15:08:52 +0000'),
(739, 0, 'Shehu Sani Commends FG Over Order To Audit NDDC', 'Politics', 'https://www.informationng.com/2019/10/shehu-sani-commends-fg-over-order-to-audit-nddc.html', 'https://www.informationng.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/shehu-sani-reacts-to-buharis-appraisal-of-jonathan.jpg', 'Former lawmaker, Senator Shehu Sani has commended the Federal Government over the directive to audit the Niger Delta Development Commission (NDDC).\nSenator Shehu Sani\nRecall that some days ago, President Muhammadu Buhari ordered the audit of the commission over the non-implementation of projects.\nAlso Read: Shehu Sani Drums Support For Planned Labour Strike\nThe former lawmaker expressed that the decision is a right step considering the debts the nation is owing.\nSee his tweet below:\n\nWith trillions of Naira in debt,the audit of the NDDC as ordered by the FG is a step in the right direction and commendable.\n&mdash; Senator Shehu Sani (@ShehuSani) October 20, 2019\n\nThe post Shehu Sani Commends FG Over Order To Audit NDDC appeared first on Information Nigeria.\n', 0, 'Mon, 21 Oct 2019 15:06:00 +0000'),
(740, 0, 'Fuji Singer, Pasuma Pens Sweet Words To Mark Daughter’s Birthday', 'Entertainment', 'https://www.informationng.com/2019/10/fuji-singer-pasuma-pens-sweet-words-to-mark-daughters-birthday.html', 'https://alexis.lindaikejisblog.com/photos/shares/5ac673c04c29b.PNG', 'Fuji Singer Pasuma\nPopular Nigerian Fuji Icon, Pasuma has written sweet words of prayer to celebrate with his daughter who added another year to her age.\nTaking to his Instagram, he shared a photo of his daughter, Barakat Ajoke Oyindamola with words of prayer.\nIn his tweet, he prayed to God for her heart&#8217;s desire to be granted while he reminded her that he loves her and supports her.\nREAD ALSO &#8211; How Yinka Quadri, Liz Da Silva, Dayo Amusa, Pasuma stormed MC Oluomo’s daughter’s wedding introduction (photos)\nIn his own words: &#8220;HBD Barakat Ajoke Oyindamola,Blessing Child May God Almighty grant yhu yhur heart desires @oyin_cookie(Amin )Enjoy yhur cake day dear, daddy loves yhu &#8221;\nSee The Post Here:\nhttps://www.instagram.com/p/B34GgOGprhY/?utm_source=ig_web_copy_link\n&nbsp;\nThe post Fuji Singer, Pasuma Pens Sweet Words To Mark Daughter&#8217;s Birthday appeared first on Information Nigeria.\n', 0, 'Mon, 21 Oct 2019 15:03:38 +0000'),
(741, 0, 'Comedian Akpororo Flaunts New Car, Promotes New Song', 'Lifestyle', 'https://www.informationng.com/2019/10/comedian-akpororo-flaunts-new-car-promotes-new-song.html', 'http://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/Akpororo.png', 'Nigerian Comedian Akpororo\nPopular Nigerian Comedian Akpororo has shared a photo of himself with his new car on his Instagram.\nThe comedian who recently bought a car in celebration of his wife&#8217;s birthday has now bought one for himself.\nAttributing his success to God and his favour to his family, Akpororo shared the photo of his new car to his followers and fans alike.\nREAD ALSO &#8211; Nigerian Comedian Akpororo Surprises His Wife With Brand New SUV\nHe also used the medium to promote his latest single, &#8220;#Iserveaverybiggod&#8221; which is now available for download on all digital platforms.\nAccording to him: &#8220;Indeed I serve a very big God. All through the year, God has been good to me and my family. #iserveaverybiggod is my testimony of God’s grace and favor. This is my latest toy #iserveaverybiggod is ready for download on all digital platforms&#8230; get link on my bio #roroking #roronation.&#8221;\nSee His Post Here:\n\n  \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n View this post on Instagram\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n \n Indeed I serve a very big God. All through the year God has been good to me and my family. #iserveaverybiggod is my testimony of God’s grace and favor. This is my latest  toy #iserveaverybiggod is ready for download on all digital platforms&#8230; get link on my bio #roroking #roronation\nA post shared by  Jephthahakpororo@yahoo.com (@akpororo) on Oct 21, 2019 at 5:12am PDT\n\n\n\nThe post Comedian Akpororo Flaunts New Car, Promotes New Song appeared first on Information Nigeria.\n', 0, 'Mon, 21 Oct 2019 14:13:35 +0000'),
(742, 0, 'No Ministry Of Early Salary Payment In Gombe — Govt', 'Trending', 'https://www.informationng.com/2019/10/no-ministry-of-early-salary-payment-in-gombe-govt.html', 'https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Gombe.jpg', 'Gombe Ministry of Early Salary Payment\nThe government of Gombe state has reacted to a trending social media picture of a bus with the inscription: “Ministry of Early Salary Payment, Gombe state”.\n\n\n\n\n\nIsmaila Misilli, senior special assistant to the governor on media and publicity, said: “Our attention has been drawn to a photograph of a bus with a superimposed inscription of ‘ministry of early salary payment’ proudly belonging to Gombe state. ”\n“This is nothing but fake and reeks of desperados. Gombe state has no such ministry. Members of the public are warned to disregard the fake photo and desist from circulating it.\n“For the records, Gombe at the moment has 21 ministries sequel to executive order 1 issued by governor Muhammadu Inuwa Yahaya as follows:\nRead Also: Nigeria doesn&#8217;t need prayers; Gombe State Governor, Ibrahim Dankwambo\n\nMinistry of agriculture and husbandry\nMinistry of commerce, industry and tourism\nMinistry of education\nMinistry of higher education\nMinistry of finance and economic development\nMinistry of health\nMinistry of information and culture\nMinistry of justice\nMinistry of Lands and survey\nMinistry of local government and chieftaincy affairs\nMinistry of science, technology and innovation.\nMinistry of special duties\nMinistry of Works and transport\nMinistry of youths and sports development\nMinistry of women affairs and social development\nMinistry of water resources\nMinistry of rural, community development and cooperatives\nMinistry of internal security and ethical orientation\nMinistry of energy and mineral resources\nMinistry of environment and forest resources\nMinistry of housing and urban development.\n\n\n\n\n\n\nThe post No Ministry Of Early Salary Payment In Gombe — Govt appeared first on Information Nigeria.\n', 0, 'Mon, 21 Oct 2019 14:04:15 +0000'),
(743, 0, 'Woman Shares Details Of Lady In Pastor Wilson Viral Sex Video (Photo)', 'News', 'https://www.informationng.com/2019/10/woman-shares-details-of-lady-in-pastor-wilson-viral-sex-video-photo.html', 'https://www.informationng.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/10430814_img20191021125442882_jpeg3fb982eaa1a3439bca7022bcefa6ab6b.jpg', 'Pastor Wilson and Alleged Lady In Vidoe\nAn Internet user has shared a Facebook profile of the person she believes to be the lady in Pastor Wison&#8217;s Viral sex video.\nShe shared the profile and speculated that the lady was the recipient of the oral sex the Pastor was filmed having.\nREAD ALSO &#8211; ‘Lady In Pastor Wilson’s Sex Video Is The Daughter Of His Wife’s Best Friend&#8217;s – Pastor Thaddeus (Video)\nIn the video, Pastor David Wilson of the BibleWay Ministries &amp; World Out Reach, Inc., Texas, was clearly engrossed the act that he seems not aware he was being recorded.\nThe Internet user shared the profile whose name is &#8220;Corinthia Edwards.&#8221;\nApparently, Corinthia was promised a lead role by the pastor and when things didn&#8217;t go as planned, she leaked the video.\nSee Her Post Here:\n\n\nThe post Woman Shares Details Of Lady In Pastor Wilson Viral Sex Video (Photo) appeared first on Information Nigeria.\n', 0, 'Mon, 21 Oct 2019 13:59:43 +0000');
