(1051, 0, 'Delivery Man Gets Pranked, Goes Unclad After Getting Aroused By Oyibo Woman (Video)', 'Trending', 'https://www.informationng.com/2019/10/delivery-man-gets-pranked-goes-unclad-after-getting-aroused-by-oyibo-woman-video.html', 'https://www.informationng.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/72490018_2117811078525546_6879113287383023261_n.jpg', 'A delivery man from an undisclosed food outlet stripped to his boxers after he was sexually aroused by a white woman in a skit by popular comedian, Zion Ubani alias Zfancy.\nThe delivery man and the lady\nIn the skit, the white woman identified as Catherine, who she is also from Russia, seduced the man in a bikini and fishnet.\nThe delivery man then charged the lady 20, 000 to spend 1 hour in the room with her.\nThe lady and the man both took turns in taking off pieces of their clothes.\nHowever, while the man was about to pull off his trousers, Zfancy appeared, pretending to be Catherine&#8217;s boyfriend.\nThe delivery man got on his knees pleading with the comedian unknown to him that it was all planned.\nRead Also: Photos, Details Of Lady In Viral Video With Pastor Wilson Emerges Online\nWatch the hilarious video below:\n\n  \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n View this post on Instagram\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n \n This is a bloody PRANK  : @zfancytv\nA post shared by  Tunde Ednut (@tundeednut) on Oct 21, 2019 at 8:31am PDT\n\n\n\nThe post Delivery Man Gets Pranked, Goes Unclad After Getting Aroused By Oyibo Woman (Video) appeared first on Information Nigeria.\n', 0, 'Mon, 21 Oct 2019 18:59:30 +0000'),
(1052, 0, 'Fans Blast Ghanaian Singer For Flashing Her Sanitary Pad While Perfoming In Skimpy Dress (Video)', 'Entertainment', 'https://www.informationng.com/2019/10/fans-blast-ghanaian-singer-for-flashing-her-sanitary-pad-while-perfoming-in-skimpy-dress-video.html', 'https://www.informationng.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/images-19-1.jpeg', 'A Ghanaian singer, Fantana has been put on blast by web users after she accidentally flashed her sanitary pad while performing in a skimpy dress on stage.\nGhanaian singer, Fantana\nIt appears the female musician unexpectedly her period while singing at Shatta Wale&#8217;s Reign Concert and Wonder Boy album launch.\nReports claim the sanitary pad did not fit in quite well in the panties the musicisn had worn and this caused her to suffer a wardrobe malfunction.\nRead Also: “Daddy Of The Year” – Chioma Shares Video Of Herself With Davido By Her Side In Hospital (Video)\nSee the reactions and video below:\n\n\n&nbsp;\nThe post Fans Blast Ghanaian Singer For Flashing Her Sanitary Pad While Perfoming In Skimpy Dress (Video) appeared first on Information Nigeria.\n', 0, 'Mon, 21 Oct 2019 18:53:21 +0000'),
(1053, 0, 'Nigerian Comedian Blasts Ubi Franklin For Slapping Him', 'Metro News', 'https://www.informationng.com/2019/10/nigerian-comedian-blasts-ubi-franklin-for-slapping-him.html', 'https://www.informationng.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Ubi-Franklin-jacked-and-slapped-me-backstage-for-making-a-joke-about-him-Comedian-Omini-Aho-cries-out.jpeg', 'A Nigerian comedian, Omini Aho has blasted music executive, Ubi Franklin for allegedly slapping him backstage an event in Lagos.\nUbi Franklin and Comedian Omini\nIt appears the comedian had made a joke about the music executive, who in turn, was quite displeased about it.\nThe comedian had taken to Instagram to call out Franklin and to share his side of the story.\nOmini wrote,\n&#8220;The job of a comedian is to find humor in every situation and put it out for the audience, I did a joke yesterday and Ubi came backstage and jacked me, I was trying to be calm because I didn’t want to disrupt Acapella’s show, the next thing was a slap (Gbosa).\nUbi don slap Omini Aho, chia, as I wan retaliate Na so bouncer hold us, I think Ubi don bribe the bouncer, I have nothing personal about Ubi before then but now, I have everything personal against him, the truth is that the JOKE is always on something or someone, no comedian goes out with the intention of hurting anyone, the aim is to generate laughter but Ubi has shown that his mind is quick to anger as his ejaculation.\nIf we want to go by Ubi’s way, Tubaba would have killed almost every comedian, Donald Trump would have killed almost every comedian, especially in America, open your mind, it’s just a joke.&#8221;\nSee the post below:\n\n\n  \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n View this post on Instagram\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n \n Comedian #Ominiaho declares #UbiFranklin a dog for slapping him over a joke. [Swipe]\nA post shared by  Instablog9ja (@instablog9ja) on Oct 21, 2019 at 8:31am PDT\n\n\n\nThe post Nigerian Comedian Blasts Ubi Franklin For Slapping Him appeared first on Information Nigeria.\n', 0, 'Mon, 21 Oct 2019 18:52:51 +0000'),
(1054, 0, 'It Is Unfortunate No One Is Willing To Stand As Sowore’s Surety: Judge', 'News', 'https://www.informationng.com/2019/10/it-is-unfortunate-no-one-is-willing-to-stand-as-sowores-surety-judge.html', 'https://www.informationng.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/5d91bcd112e1b.png', 'Founder of Sahara Reporters Omoyele Sowore\nJustice Ijeoma Ojukwu of the federal high court, Abuja has expressed concern over the fact that Omoyele Sowore, convener of #RevolutionNow Movement, has not met his bail conditions.\nThe judge while ruling on the application for variation of the bail conditions on Monday, said: “Considering the pedigree of the first defendant as observed in his application, it is rather unfortunate that no one is willing to stand as his surety on those terms.\n“On the other hand, it creates an assumption that despite the pedigree of the first defendant, none of his best associates is willing to stand for him. This poses a cause for concern.”\nShe explained that bail sum is not required to be deposited but when a court makes an order for security, the secure money is later returned to the owner (surety).\nThe activist has been in custody of the Department of State Services (DSS) since August 3 when he was arrested in Lagos.\nRead Also: Abuja Court Softens Sowore’s Bail Conditions\nFemi Falana, Sowore’s counsel, had approached the court seeking a variation to the previous bail conditions which he said could not be met.\nOjukwu reviewed Sowore’s bail conditions and set aside the previous order which directed one of Sowore’s surety to deposit N50m.\nShe also reduced the bail sum of Olawale Bakare, the second defendant, to N30m instead of the initial N50m.\nHowever, she refused to vary all the other conditions for bail.\nAmong the other conditions of the for bail are two sureties who must be resident in Abuja and have landed properties within the federal capital territory (FCT).\nThe court had held that the sureties must deposit original documents of those properties in the court registry.\nThe judge barred him from travelling outside Abuja and also stopped him from addressing any rally.\nThe post It Is Unfortunate No One Is Willing To Stand As Sowore&#8217;s Surety: Judge appeared first on Information Nigeria.\n', 0, 'Mon, 21 Oct 2019 18:49:10 +0000'),
(1055, 0, 'Breaking: Court Orders Forfeiture Of Saraki’s Properties In Lagos', 'News', 'https://www.informationng.com/2019/10/breaking-court-orders-forfeiture-of-two-of-sarakis-properties-in-lagos.html', 'https://www.informationng.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/saraki.jpg', 'Bukola Saraki\nA federal high court sitting in Lagos has ordered the temporary forfeiture of two properties belonging to Bukola Saraki, senate president of the 8th National Assembly at Ikoyi Lagos state.\nThis was after a counsel of the Economic and Financial Crimes Commission ( EFCC), Nnaemeka Omewa approached the court, seeking an order of interim forfeiture of the properties located at 17A McDonald Road, Ikoyi, Eti Osa local government area of Lagos.\nHe had told the court that they were acquired through “proceeds of unlawful activities”.\nRead Also: Why Saraki Blocked Confirmation Of EFCC Chairman, Magu: Alaafin Of Oyo\nSome other reliefs the EFCC sought  included, “an order of this honourable Court forfeiting to the Federal Government of Nigeria landed property with appurtenances situate, lying and known as No. 17A McDonald Road, Ikoyi, Eti Osa Local Government Area of Lagos State found and recovered from the respondent which property is reasonably suspected to have been acquired with proceeds of unlawful activity”.\nThe post Breaking: Court Orders Forfeiture Of Saraki&#8217;s Properties In Lagos appeared first on Information Nigeria.\n', 0, 'Mon, 21 Oct 2019 15:33:15 +0000'),
(1056, 0, 'Glory Osei, Muyiwa Folorunsho Of LandLagos Attacked For Allegedly Defrauding Employees', 'Gossip', 'https://www.informationng.com/2019/10/glory-osei-muyiwa-folorunsho-of-landlagos-attacked-for-allegedly-defrauding-employees.html', 'https://www.informationng.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/10431260_gloryoseiandmuyiwafolorunsho_pngf88e4eef2bb70be82d7736b56f6e55a6-1.png', 'Popular entrepreneurs, Muyiwa Folorunsho and Glory Osei, have been accused of fraud and maltreatment of staff by their former employees.\nGlory Osei and Muyiwa Folorunsho\nThe twitter user also alleged that the two entrepreneurs are married couple.\nAlso Read: Glory Osei Reacts To Former Employee’s Fraud Allegations\nTwitter is currently buzzing as a former employee of the duo accuses them of fraud, toxic work environment, deducting from their salaries or sacking them over trivial mistakes and more.\nSee post below:\n\n&#8211; Lady calls out a job owner , Glory Osei ,and her husband, Muyiwa ,for alleged scam and maltreatment of staff and partners. pic.twitter.com/WOG3EoSNCA\n&mdash; SubDeliveryZone (@SubDeliveryZone) October 21, 2019\n\n&nbsp;\nThe post Glory Osei, Muyiwa Folorunsho Of LandLagos Attacked For Allegedly Defrauding Employees appeared first on Information Nigeria.\n', 0, 'Mon, 21 Oct 2019 15:32:48 +0000'),
(1057, 0, 'Abuja Court Softens Sowore’s Bail Conditions', 'News', 'https://www.informationng.com/2019/10/abuja-court-softens-sowores-bail-conditions.html', 'https://www.informationng.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/sowore-777x437.jpg', 'Omoyele Sowore\nA Federal High Court in Abuja has reduced the bail conditions on the convener of #RevolutionNow, Omoyele Sowore and his co-defendant, Olawale Bakare over charges of treason.\nThe condition was reduced by Justice Ijeoma Ojukwu on Monday. She reduced Sowore’s bail bond to the N50m down from N100m, while Bakare’s bail was reduced from N50m to N20m.\nRead Also: 13th Headies: Falz Advocates For Sowore&#8217;s Release After Receiving Award (Video)\nOjukwu also ordered that sureties to the defendants are no longer expected to deposit evidence of the funds with the court registrar.\nThe post Abuja Court Softens Sowore&#8217;s Bail Conditions appeared first on Information Nigeria.\n', 0, 'Mon, 21 Oct 2019 15:31:29 +0000'),
(1058, 0, 'Davido’s Son Models For Mario And Juliet As Brand Ambassador', 'Entertainment', 'https://www.informationng.com/2019/10/davidos-son-models-for-mario-and-juliet-as-brand-ambassador.html', 'https://www.informationng.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Davidos-new-baby.png', 'Adedeji Ifeanyi Adeleke, Davido’s newborn baby boy has been announced brand ambassador to Mario and Juliet Diapers.\nDavido welcomes baby boy\nThe artist and Chioma’s son, David Adedeji Ifeanyi Adeleke got a planned endorsement with baby products brand, Mario and Juliet a month before he was born.\nAlso Read: Chioma Shares A Glimpse Of Her Son Moving His Hands (Video)\nFew hours after the baby&#8217;s arrival was announced, the company revealed him as a Brand Ambassador.\nSee post below:\nDavido and son\n&nbsp;\nThe post Davido’s Son Models For Mario And Juliet As Brand Ambassador appeared first on Information Nigeria.\n', 0, 'Mon, 21 Oct 2019 15:29:12 +0000'),
(1059, 0, 'Yoruba Is Derived From ‘Yariba’ And It Means ‘Shady, Unreliable’: Fani-Kayode', 'Trending', 'https://www.informationng.com/2019/10/yoruba-is-derived-from-yariba-and-it-means-shady-unreliable-fani-kayode.html', 'https://www.informationng.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/ffk.jpg', 'Femi Fani Kayode\nA former minister of aviation, Femi Fani-Kayode has said that the name &#8220;Yoruba&#8221; is derived from &#8220;Yariba&#8221; and it means &#8220;shady and unreliable&#8221;.\nAccording to Fani-Kayode, &#8216;Yariba&#8217; is the name given to the Southwest(SW) by the Fulani. He added that while the Southeast rejected the name &#8216;Yamiri&#8217; given to them by the Fulani, the Southwest accepted theirs.\nHe said in a few tweets on Monday thus:\nTwo names that the Fulani gave to southerners: &#8220;Yamiri&#8221;, in reference to SE and &#8220;Yariba&#8221; in reference to SW. The SE rejected that name but the SW accepted it. The name &#8220;Yoruba&#8221; derives from &#8220;Yariba&#8221; and it means &#8220;shady and unreliable&#8221;. I reject that strange name and label.\nI am not a &#8220;Yariba&#8221; or &#8220;Yoruba&#8221; but an &#8220;Omo Karo Jire&#8221; or an &#8220;Oduduwan&#8221; and my language are not &#8220;Yoruba&#8221; but &#8220;Anago&#8221;. We are what we call ourselves. We are not &#8220;shady and unreliable&#8221;(Yariba) and we must not accept names that are given to us by our historical adversaries&#8230;\n&#8230;Any Omo Karo Jire or Oduduwan that continues to call himself a &#8220;Yoruba&#8221; is lost and does not know the implications of what he is doing to his own people. He is simply affirming and confirming an insulting label that has deep sinister, mystical and spiritual connotations&#8230;\nRead Also:Igbo Women Were Placed On Earth For Yoruba Men: Ycee\n&#8230;The word &#8220;Yoruba&#8221; did not even exist until the 18th century and even then most of the tribes of the SW, including the Oyo&#8217;s, rejected it due to its origin and meaning. The word &#8220;Yoruba&#8221; is alien to our culture and not known in the Anago language. Oduduwans please take note.\n\n&#8230;.I am not a &quot;Yariba&quot; or &quot;Yoruba&quot; but an &quot;Omo Karo Jire&quot; or an &quot;Oduduwan&quot; and my lanuage is not &quot;Yoruba&quot; but &quot;Anago&quot;. We are what we call ourselves. We are not &quot;shady and uneliable&quot;(Yariba) and we must not accept names that are given to us by our historical adversaries&#8230;\n&mdash; Femi Fani-Kayode (@realFFK) October 21, 2019\n\n\n&#8230;The word &quot;Yoruba&quot; did not even exist until the 18th century and even then most of the tribes of the SW, including the Oyo&#39;s, rejected it due to its origin and meaning. The word &quot;Yoruba&quot; is alien to our culture and not known in the Anago language. Oduduwans please take note.\n&mdash; Femi Fani-Kayode (@realFFK) October 21, 2019\n\nThe post Yoruba Is Derived From &#8216;Yariba&#8217; And It Means &#8216;Shady, Unreliable&#8217;: Fani-Kayode appeared first on Information Nigeria.\n', 0, 'Mon, 21 Oct 2019 15:18:23 +0000'),
(1060, 0, 'Strange Moments Two Cats Disappear At Aba Market [Video]', 'Metro News', 'https://www.informationng.com/2019/10/strange-moments-two-cats-disappear-at-aba-market-video.html', 'https://www.informationng.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/cat.jpg', 'Cat\nA CCTV footage has shown the mysterious moment two cats disappeared at a market in Aba, Abia state.\nIn the video shared via Twitter, two cats were seen strolling through an empty corridor of shops, when they suddenly disappeared at the same time.\nHowever, some social media users have argued that the video might have been tampered with, while some are of the firm belief that the cat really disappears.\nRead Also: Brides Catches Groom Sexually Assaulting Her Bridesmaid; Goes Ahead To Marry Him\nSee video below\n\n&#8211; CCTV captures the moment two cats disappeared at a market in Aba ,Abia state. pic.twitter.com/InUeGnQi4v\n&mdash; SubDeliveryZone (@SubDeliveryZone) October 21, 2019\n\nThe post Strange Moments Two Cats Disappear At Aba Market [Video] appeared first on Information Nigeria.\n', 0, 'Mon, 21 Oct 2019 15:16:48 +0000'),
(1061, 0, 'Mungo Park Didn’t Discover Source Of River Niger, Stop The Brainwash: Reno Omokri', 'Education', 'https://www.informationng.com/2019/10/mungo-park-didnt-discover-source-of-river-niger-stop-the-brainwash-reno-omokri.html', 'https://www.informationng.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Reno-book-signing-700x466.jpg', 'Popular social media activist, Reno Omokri has queried the decision of curicculum makers over the teaching that Mungo Park discovered the source of River Niger.\nNigerian author, Reno Omokri\nAccording to the activist, the common saying that Mungo Park discovered the source of River Niger is a historical lie.\nAlso Read: Reno Omokri Helps Victim Of Onitsha Fire Outbreak (Video)\nHe went further to express that the continuous teaching of that knowledge in school is a deliberate attempt to brainwash Nigerians.\nSee his post below:\n\nWhy does Nigeria still allow that colonial historical lie that Mungo Park discovered the source of the River Niger to be taught in schools? How can Nigeria continue to brainwash her own children with a colonial lie?\n                  #TableShaker#FreeLeahSharibu #RenosNuggets\n&mdash; Reno Omokri (@renoomokri) October 21, 2019\n\nThe post Mungo Park Didn&#8217;t Discover Source Of River Niger, Stop The Brainwash: Reno Omokri appeared first on Information Nigeria.\n', 0, 'Mon, 21 Oct 2019 15:13:41 +0000'),
(1062, 0, 'Prophet Jailed For Stealing Member’s International Passport', 'Metro News', 'https://www.informationng.com/2019/10/prophet-jailed-for-stealing-members-international-passport.html', 'https://www.informationng.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/court-jails-woman-for-exposing-her-cheating-boss-who-was-having-affair-with-a-colleague.jpg', '\nA Prophet in Zimbabwe has been sentenced to 6 months in prison after he stole the passport of a member of his congregation and used it to travel to South Africa under the falsehood that he was praying for it.\nThe prophet identified as Shepherd Mbili was convicted by a Bulawayo Magistrate, Zimbabwe after he pleaded guilty to the charges levelled against him.\nRead Also: Photos, Details Of Lady In Viral Video With Pastor Wilson Emerges Online\nThe prophet was said to have asked Mr Godknows to bring his passport and academic certificates for anointing, he then prayed for it and advised the complainant not to open the envelope fully knowing that he had stolen his passport.\n“He told me not to open the envelope until I’m ready to use it On the 6th of October I opened the envelope to check the last date I went to Zambia and I found out that my passport was missing. I went to look for Prophet Mbili and his wife told me that he had travelled to South Africa with my passport and would be back soon” said the congregant whose passport was stolen.\nThe post Prophet Jailed For Stealing Member&#8217;s International Passport appeared first on Information Nigeria.\n', 0, 'Mon, 21 Oct 2019 15:11:58 +0000'),
(1063, 0, 'Wizkid Gushes About 3rd Babymama, Jada Pollock', 'Entertainment', 'https://www.informationng.com/2019/10/wizkid-gushes-about-3rd-babymama-jada-pollock.html', 'https://www.informationng.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/b7Zk9kpTURBXy9lZjY3ZWIxMDc3Y2M5YmRkNmU5ZGU1OTdiZjU4NmI2Yy5qcGeRkwXNAxTNAbyBoTAB.jpg', 'Nigerian Music Star Wizkid\nNigerian singer, Ayo Balogun who is popularly known as Wizkid has taken to social media to gush about his baby mama, Jada Pollock.\nThe singer who had a very successful outing at the WizkidFest, which held at the O2 arena, London over the weekend, toom to Twitter to wish Jada, the mother of his son, Zion, a happy birthday with so much love.\nRead Also: Wizkid Beats Me, Leaves Me With Bruises: 3rd Baby Mama, Jada Pollock Cries Out\nIt will be recalled that Pollock had in July this year, accused the Starboy via social media of abusing her physically and later claimed that her account was hacked.\nCelebrating the mother of his third child, he described her as a superwoman whom he got forever.\nHe wrote: Thank you, Jada! Thank you, Jada! Thank You, Jada!  Happy birthday! love you !!  superwoman!! My bad charge. Got you forever!!\n\nThank you Jada! Thank you Jada ! Thank You Jada! ?? Happy birthday!  love you !! ???????? superwoman!!  My bad charge. Got you forever !\n&mdash; Wizkid (@wizkidayo) October 21, 2019\n\n&nbsp;\nThe post Wizkid Gushes About 3rd Babymama, Jada Pollock appeared first on Information Nigeria.\n', 0, 'Mon, 21 Oct 2019 15:08:52 +0000'),
(1064, 0, 'Shehu Sani Commends FG Over Order To Audit NDDC', 'Politics', 'https://www.informationng.com/2019/10/shehu-sani-commends-fg-over-order-to-audit-nddc.html', 'https://www.informationng.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/shehu-sani-reacts-to-buharis-appraisal-of-jonathan.jpg', 'Former lawmaker, Senator Shehu Sani has commended the Federal Government over the directive to audit the Niger Delta Development Commission (NDDC).\nSenator Shehu Sani\nRecall that some days ago, President Muhammadu Buhari ordered the audit of the commission over the non-implementation of projects.\nAlso Read: Shehu Sani Drums Support For Planned Labour Strike\nThe former lawmaker expressed that the decision is a right step considering the debts the nation is owing.\nSee his tweet below:\n\nWith trillions of Naira in debt,the audit of the NDDC as ordered by the FG is a step in the right direction and commendable.\n&mdash; Senator Shehu Sani (@ShehuSani) October 20, 2019\n\nThe post Shehu Sani Commends FG Over Order To Audit NDDC appeared first on Information Nigeria.\n', 0, 'Mon, 21 Oct 2019 15:06:00 +0000'),
(1065, 0, 'Fuji Singer, Pasuma Pens Sweet Words To Mark Daughter’s Birthday', 'Entertainment', 'https://www.informationng.com/2019/10/fuji-singer-pasuma-pens-sweet-words-to-mark-daughters-birthday.html', 'https://alexis.lindaikejisblog.com/photos/shares/5ac673c04c29b.PNG', 'Fuji Singer Pasuma\nPopular Nigerian Fuji Icon, Pasuma has written sweet words of prayer to celebrate with his daughter who added another year to her age.\nTaking to his Instagram, he shared a photo of his daughter, Barakat Ajoke Oyindamola with words of prayer.\nIn his tweet, he prayed to God for her heart&#8217;s desire to be granted while he reminded her that he loves her and supports her.\nREAD ALSO &#8211; How Yinka Quadri, Liz Da Silva, Dayo Amusa, Pasuma stormed MC Oluomo’s daughter’s wedding introduction (photos)\nIn his own words: &#8220;HBD Barakat Ajoke Oyindamola,Blessing Child May God Almighty grant yhu yhur heart desires @oyin_cookie(Amin )Enjoy yhur cake day dear, daddy loves yhu &#8221;\nSee The Post Here:\nhttps://www.instagram.com/p/B34GgOGprhY/?utm_source=ig_web_copy_link\n&nbsp;\nThe post Fuji Singer, Pasuma Pens Sweet Words To Mark Daughter&#8217;s Birthday appeared first on Information Nigeria.\n', 0, 'Mon, 21 Oct 2019 15:03:38 +0000'),
(1066, 0, 'Comedian Akpororo Flaunts New Car, Promotes New Song', 'Lifestyle', 'https://www.informationng.com/2019/10/comedian-akpororo-flaunts-new-car-promotes-new-song.html', 'http://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/Akpororo.png', 'Nigerian Comedian Akpororo\nPopular Nigerian Comedian Akpororo has shared a photo of himself with his new car on his Instagram.\nThe comedian who recently bought a car in celebration of his wife&#8217;s birthday has now bought one for himself.\nAttributing his success to God and his favour to his family, Akpororo shared the photo of his new car to his followers and fans alike.\nREAD ALSO &#8211; Nigerian Comedian Akpororo Surprises His Wife With Brand New SUV\nHe also used the medium to promote his latest single, &#8220;#Iserveaverybiggod&#8221; which is now available for download on all digital platforms.\nAccording to him: &#8220;Indeed I serve a very big God. All through the year, God has been good to me and my family. #iserveaverybiggod is my testimony of God’s grace and favor. This is my latest toy #iserveaverybiggod is ready for download on all digital platforms&#8230; get link on my bio #roroking #roronation.&#8221;\nSee His Post Here:\n\n  \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n View this post on Instagram\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n \n Indeed I serve a very big God. All through the year God has been good to me and my family. #iserveaverybiggod is my testimony of God’s grace and favor. This is my latest  toy #iserveaverybiggod is ready for download on all digital platforms&#8230; get link on my bio #roroking #roronation\nA post shared by  Jephthahakpororo@yahoo.com (@akpororo) on Oct 21, 2019 at 5:12am PDT\n\n\n\nThe post Comedian Akpororo Flaunts New Car, Promotes New Song appeared first on Information Nigeria.\n', 0, 'Mon, 21 Oct 2019 14:13:35 +0000'),
(1067, 0, 'No Ministry Of Early Salary Payment In Gombe — Govt', 'Trending', 'https://www.informationng.com/2019/10/no-ministry-of-early-salary-payment-in-gombe-govt.html', 'https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Gombe.jpg', 'Gombe Ministry of Early Salary Payment\nThe government of Gombe state has reacted to a trending social media picture of a bus with the inscription: “Ministry of Early Salary Payment, Gombe state”.\n\n\n\n\n\nIsmaila Misilli, senior special assistant to the governor on media and publicity, said: “Our attention has been drawn to a photograph of a bus with a superimposed inscription of ‘ministry of early salary payment’ proudly belonging to Gombe state. ”\n“This is nothing but fake and reeks of desperados. Gombe state has no such ministry. Members of the public are warned to disregard the fake photo and desist from circulating it.\n“For the records, Gombe at the moment has 21 ministries sequel to executive order 1 issued by governor Muhammadu Inuwa Yahaya as follows:\nRead Also: Nigeria doesn&#8217;t need prayers; Gombe State Governor, Ibrahim Dankwambo\n\nMinistry of agriculture and husbandry\nMinistry of commerce, industry and tourism\nMinistry of education\nMinistry of higher education\nMinistry of finance and economic development\nMinistry of health\nMinistry of information and culture\nMinistry of justice\nMinistry of Lands and survey\nMinistry of local government and chieftaincy affairs\nMinistry of science, technology and innovation.\nMinistry of special duties\nMinistry of Works and transport\nMinistry of youths and sports development\nMinistry of women affairs and social development\nMinistry of water resources\nMinistry of rural, community development and cooperatives\nMinistry of internal security and ethical orientation\nMinistry of energy and mineral resources\nMinistry of environment and forest resources\nMinistry of housing and urban development.\n\n\n\n\n\n\nThe post No Ministry Of Early Salary Payment In Gombe — Govt appeared first on Information Nigeria.\n', 0, 'Mon, 21 Oct 2019 14:04:15 +0000'),
(1068, 0, 'Woman Shares Details Of Lady In Pastor Wilson Viral Sex Video (Photo)', 'News', 'https://www.informationng.com/2019/10/woman-shares-details-of-lady-in-pastor-wilson-viral-sex-video-photo.html', 'https://www.informationng.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/10430814_img20191021125442882_jpeg3fb982eaa1a3439bca7022bcefa6ab6b.jpg', 'Pastor Wilson and Alleged Lady In Vidoe\nAn Internet user has shared a Facebook profile of the person she believes to be the lady in Pastor Wison&#8217;s Viral sex video.\nShe shared the profile and speculated that the lady was the recipient of the oral sex the Pastor was filmed having.\nREAD ALSO &#8211; ‘Lady In Pastor Wilson’s Sex Video Is The Daughter Of His Wife’s Best Friend&#8217;s – Pastor Thaddeus (Video)\nIn the video, Pastor David Wilson of the BibleWay Ministries &amp; World Out Reach, Inc., Texas, was clearly engrossed the act that he seems not aware he was being recorded.\nThe Internet user shared the profile whose name is &#8220;Corinthia Edwards.&#8221;\nApparently, Corinthia was promised a lead role by the pastor and when things didn&#8217;t go as planned, she leaked the video.\nSee Her Post Here:\n\n\nThe post Woman Shares Details Of Lady In Pastor Wilson Viral Sex Video (Photo) appeared first on Information Nigeria.\n', 0, 'Mon, 21 Oct 2019 13:59:43 +0000');
