(1298, 0, 'No Ministry Of Early Salary Payment In Gombe — Govt', 'Trending', 'https://www.informationng.com/2019/10/no-ministry-of-early-salary-payment-in-gombe-govt.html', 'https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Gombe.jpg', 'Gombe Ministry of Early Salary Payment\nThe government of Gombe state has reacted to a trending social media picture of a bus with the inscription: “Ministry of Early Salary Payment, Gombe state”.\n\n\n\n\n\nIsmaila Misilli, senior special assistant to the governor on media and publicity, said: “Our attention has been drawn to a photograph of a bus with a superimposed inscription of ‘ministry of early salary payment’ proudly belonging to Gombe state. ”\n“This is nothing but fake and reeks of desperados. Gombe state has no such ministry. Members of the public are warned to disregard the fake photo and desist from circulating it.\n“For the records, Gombe at the moment has 21 ministries sequel to executive order 1 issued by governor Muhammadu Inuwa Yahaya as follows:\nRead Also: Nigeria doesn&#8217;t need prayers; Gombe State Governor, Ibrahim Dankwambo\n\nMinistry of agriculture and husbandry\nMinistry of commerce, industry and tourism\nMinistry of education\nMinistry of higher education\nMinistry of finance and economic development\nMinistry of health\nMinistry of information and culture\nMinistry of justice\nMinistry of Lands and survey\nMinistry of local government and chieftaincy affairs\nMinistry of science, technology and innovation.\nMinistry of special duties\nMinistry of Works and transport\nMinistry of youths and sports development\nMinistry of women affairs and social development\nMinistry of water resources\nMinistry of rural, community development and cooperatives\nMinistry of internal security and ethical orientation\nMinistry of energy and mineral resources\nMinistry of environment and forest resources\nMinistry of housing and urban development.\n\n\n\n\n\n\nThe post No Ministry Of Early Salary Payment In Gombe — Govt appeared first on Information Nigeria.\n', 0, 'Mon, 21 Oct 2019 14:04:15 +0000'),
(1299, 0, 'Woman Shares Details Of Lady In Pastor Wilson Viral Sex Video (Photo)', 'News', 'https://www.informationng.com/2019/10/woman-shares-details-of-lady-in-pastor-wilson-viral-sex-video-photo.html', 'https://www.informationng.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/10430814_img20191021125442882_jpeg3fb982eaa1a3439bca7022bcefa6ab6b.jpg', 'Pastor Wilson and Alleged Lady In Vidoe\nAn Internet user has shared a Facebook profile of the person she believes to be the lady in Pastor Wison&#8217;s Viral sex video.\nShe shared the profile and speculated that the lady was the recipient of the oral sex the Pastor was filmed having.\nREAD ALSO &#8211; ‘Lady In Pastor Wilson’s Sex Video Is The Daughter Of His Wife’s Best Friend&#8217;s – Pastor Thaddeus (Video)\nIn the video, Pastor David Wilson of the BibleWay Ministries &amp; World Out Reach, Inc., Texas, was clearly engrossed the act that he seems not aware he was being recorded.\nThe Internet user shared the profile whose name is &#8220;Corinthia Edwards.&#8221;\nApparently, Corinthia was promised a lead role by the pastor and when things didn&#8217;t go as planned, she leaked the video.\nSee Her Post Here:\n\n\nThe post Woman Shares Details Of Lady In Pastor Wilson Viral Sex Video (Photo) appeared first on Information Nigeria.\n', 0, 'Mon, 21 Oct 2019 13:59:43 +0000'),
(1300, 0, 'Court Reduces Sowore’s Bail Condition To N50 Million', 'Metro News', 'https://www.informationng.com/2019/10/court-reduces-sowores-bail-condition-to-n50-million.html', 'https://www.informationng.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/5d91bcd112e1b.png', 'A Federal High Court in Abuja today heard Omoyele Sowore&#8217;s application for bail variation.\nFounder of Sahara Reporters Omoyele Sowore\nThe activist was arraigned on a four-count charge ranging from insulting President Muhammadu Buhari to money laundering.\nHe was granted bail condition of paying N150 million and had his movement restricted to Abuja.\nHowever, the activist&#8217;s camp had cried out that the bail conditions could not be met, with his lead counsel, Mr Femi Falana (SAN) describing the bails conditions as too stringent.\nAlso Read: 13th Headies: Falz Advocates For Sowore’s Release After Receiving Award (Video)\nAfter the hearing, Justice Ijeoma Ojukwu has now varied Omoyele Sowore and Olawale Bakare&#8217;s bail conditions.\nAccording to a report by SaharaReporters, Justice Ojukwu said she found it difficult to believe a man of Sowore&#8217;s pedigree did not have anyone to deposit N50 million.\nHence, Sowore bail condition was reviewed from N100 million to N50 million, and the 50 security deposits were also removed.\nThe post Court Reduces Sowore&#8217;s Bail Condition To N50 Million appeared first on Information Nigeria.\n', 0, 'Mon, 21 Oct 2019 13:56:10 +0000'),
(1301, 0, 'Court To Resume Naira Marley’s Card Fraud Case Tomorrow', 'Metro News', 'https://www.informationng.com/2019/10/court-to-resume-naira-marleys-card-fraud-case-tomorrow.html', 'https://www.informationng.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/IMG_20190510_122029.jpg', 'Popular Nigerian rapper, Azeez Fashola, a.k.a. Naira Marley is set to resume trial at the Federal High Court in Lagos for his alleged internet fraud case.\n&#8216;Puta&#8217; Crooner, Naira Marley\n“The matter is coming up tomorrow,” Wilson Uwujaren, Economic and Financial Crimes Commission ((EFCC) spokesman, said when contacted by The Guardian on Monday.\nAlso Read: ‘Legwork Is Bigger Than Headies Award’ – Naira Marley\nRecall that in May, Justice Nicholas Onweibo adjourned the singer’s internet fraud case to October 22, 23 and 24 for accelerated hearing.\nHe was granted an N2 million bail, with two sureties in a like sum.\n*Sourced from The Guardian report\nThe post Court To Resume Naira Marley&#8217;s Card Fraud Case Tomorrow appeared first on Information Nigeria.\n', 0, 'Mon, 21 Oct 2019 13:51:14 +0000'),
