(1373, 0, 'No Ministry Of Early Salary Payment In Gombe — Govt', 'Trending', 'https://www.informationng.com/2019/10/no-ministry-of-early-salary-payment-in-gombe-govt.html', 'https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Gombe.jpg', 'Gombe Ministry of Early Salary Payment\nThe government of Gombe state has reacted to a trending social media picture of a bus with the inscription: “Ministry of Early Salary Payment, Gombe state”.\n\n\n\n\n\nIsmaila Misilli, senior special assistant to the governor on media and publicity, said: “Our attention has been drawn to a photograph of a bus with a superimposed inscription of ‘ministry of early salary payment’ proudly belonging to Gombe state. ”\n“This is nothing but fake and reeks of desperados. Gombe state has no such ministry. Members of the public are warned to disregard the fake photo and desist from circulating it.\n“For the records, Gombe at the moment has 21 ministries sequel to executive order 1 issued by governor Muhammadu Inuwa Yahaya as follows:\nRead Also: Nigeria doesn&#8217;t need prayers; Gombe State Governor, Ibrahim Dankwambo\n\nMinistry of agriculture and husbandry\nMinistry of commerce, industry and tourism\nMinistry of education\nMinistry of higher education\nMinistry of finance and economic development\nMinistry of health\nMinistry of information and culture\nMinistry of justice\nMinistry of Lands and survey\nMinistry of local government and chieftaincy affairs\nMinistry of science, technology and innovation.\nMinistry of special duties\nMinistry of Works and transport\nMinistry of youths and sports development\nMinistry of women affairs and social development\nMinistry of water resources\nMinistry of rural, community development and cooperatives\nMinistry of internal security and ethical orientation\nMinistry of energy and mineral resources\nMinistry of environment and forest resources\nMinistry of housing and urban development.\n\n\n\n\n\n\nThe post No Ministry Of Early Salary Payment In Gombe — Govt appeared first on Information Nigeria.\n', 0, 'Mon, 21 Oct 2019 14:04:15 +0000'),
(1374, 0, 'Woman Shares Details Of Lady In Pastor Wilson Viral Sex Video (Photo)', 'News', 'https://www.informationng.com/2019/10/woman-shares-details-of-lady-in-pastor-wilson-viral-sex-video-photo.html', 'https://www.informationng.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/10430814_img20191021125442882_jpeg3fb982eaa1a3439bca7022bcefa6ab6b.jpg', 'Pastor Wilson and Alleged Lady In Vidoe\nAn Internet user has shared a Facebook profile of the person she believes to be the lady in Pastor Wison&#8217;s Viral sex video.\nShe shared the profile and speculated that the lady was the recipient of the oral sex the Pastor was filmed having.\nREAD ALSO &#8211; ‘Lady In Pastor Wilson’s Sex Video Is The Daughter Of His Wife’s Best Friend&#8217;s – Pastor Thaddeus (Video)\nIn the video, Pastor David Wilson of the BibleWay Ministries &amp; World Out Reach, Inc., Texas, was clearly engrossed the act that he seems not aware he was being recorded.\nThe Internet user shared the profile whose name is &#8220;Corinthia Edwards.&#8221;\nApparently, Corinthia was promised a lead role by the pastor and when things didn&#8217;t go as planned, she leaked the video.\nSee Her Post Here:\n\n\nThe post Woman Shares Details Of Lady In Pastor Wilson Viral Sex Video (Photo) appeared first on Information Nigeria.\n', 0, 'Mon, 21 Oct 2019 13:59:43 +0000'),
(1375, 0, 'Court Reduces Sowore’s Bail Condition To N50 Million', 'Metro News', 'https://www.informationng.com/2019/10/court-reduces-sowores-bail-condition-to-n50-million.html', 'https://www.informationng.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/5d91bcd112e1b.png', 'A Federal High Court in Abuja today heard Omoyele Sowore&#8217;s application for bail variation.\nFounder of Sahara Reporters Omoyele Sowore\nThe activist was arraigned on a four-count charge ranging from insulting President Muhammadu Buhari to money laundering.\nHe was granted bail condition of paying N150 million and had his movement restricted to Abuja.\nHowever, the activist&#8217;s camp had cried out that the bail conditions could not be met, with his lead counsel, Mr Femi Falana (SAN) describing the bails conditions as too stringent.\nAlso Read: 13th Headies: Falz Advocates For Sowore’s Release After Receiving Award (Video)\nAfter the hearing, Justice Ijeoma Ojukwu has now varied Omoyele Sowore and Olawale Bakare&#8217;s bail conditions.\nAccording to a report by SaharaReporters, Justice Ojukwu said she found it difficult to believe a man of Sowore&#8217;s pedigree did not have anyone to deposit N50 million.\nHence, Sowore bail condition was reviewed from N100 million to N50 million, and the 50 security deposits were also removed.\nThe post Court Reduces Sowore&#8217;s Bail Condition To N50 Million appeared first on Information Nigeria.\n', 0, 'Mon, 21 Oct 2019 13:56:10 +0000'),
(1376, 0, 'Court To Resume Naira Marley’s Card Fraud Case Tomorrow', 'Metro News', 'https://www.informationng.com/2019/10/court-to-resume-naira-marleys-card-fraud-case-tomorrow.html', 'https://www.informationng.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/IMG_20190510_122029.jpg', 'Popular Nigerian rapper, Azeez Fashola, a.k.a. Naira Marley is set to resume trial at the Federal High Court in Lagos for his alleged internet fraud case.\n&#8216;Puta&#8217; Crooner, Naira Marley\n“The matter is coming up tomorrow,” Wilson Uwujaren, Economic and Financial Crimes Commission ((EFCC) spokesman, said when contacted by The Guardian on Monday.\nAlso Read: ‘Legwork Is Bigger Than Headies Award’ – Naira Marley\nRecall that in May, Justice Nicholas Onweibo adjourned the singer’s internet fraud case to October 22, 23 and 24 for accelerated hearing.\nHe was granted an N2 million bail, with two sureties in a like sum.\n*Sourced from The Guardian report\nThe post Court To Resume Naira Marley&#8217;s Card Fraud Case Tomorrow appeared first on Information Nigeria.\n', 0, 'Mon, 21 Oct 2019 13:51:14 +0000'),
(1377, 0, 'Photos, Details Of Lady In Viral Video With Pastor Wilson Emerges Online', 'Trending', 'https://www.informationng.com/2019/10/photos-details-of-lady-in-viral-video-with-pastor-wilson-emerges-online.html', 'https://www.informationng.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Pastor-David-Wilson-R-Corinthia-edwards-M-and-his-wife.jpg', 'Photos and details of the lady allegedly in Pastor Wilson&#8217;s sex tape whom he was feasting on has emerged on the internet.\nPastor Wilson and Corinthia Edwards\nAccording to reports, the woman, Corinthia Edwards is said to be the daughter of the best-friend to the clergyman&#8217;s wife and a screenshot of her Facebook profile shows she lives in the city as the pastor.\nThe two were reportedly having an affair for a while and the pastor had allegedly given his words to make her a leader in the church choir but he failed to fulfil his promise.\nDuring one of their sexcapades, the lady filmed the video.\nEdwards, who was upset at the controversial clergyman, released the clip on the internet.\nTo make matters worse, the lady had also shared a photo of herself smiling with the words:\n“You’d be smiling like this too if Pastor Williams wrote the Lord’s Prayer in calligraphy on your south mouth with his tongue.”\nThe lady has since taken down all her social media accounts including Facebook and Instagram.\nRead Also: Chioma Shares A Glimpse Of Her Son Moving His Hands (Video)\nSee the post below:\n\nThe post Photos, Details Of Lady In Viral Video With Pastor Wilson Emerges Online appeared first on Information Nigeria.\n', 0, 'Mon, 21 Oct 2019 13:48:11 +0000'),
(1378, 0, 'I’m Still A Virgin, Waiting For My Wedding Night: Bobrisky', 'Entertainment', 'https://www.informationng.com/2019/10/im-still-a-virgin-waiting-for-my-wedding-night-bobrisky.html', 'https://www.informationng.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/bobrisky-1-700x700-600x600.jpg', 'Popular male barbie and crossdresser, Bobrisky has revealed on his Instagram page that he is still a virgin.\nNigerian Cross-dresser Bobrisky\nThe popular crossdresser expressed that the weather is cold and he needed to cuddle up with to keep himself warn.\nAlso Read: Bobrisky Hangs Out With BBNaija Winner, Mercy (Video)\nHe, however, expressed that despite his desire, he is still a virgin waiting for his wedding night.\nSee his post below:\n\n  \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n View this post on Instagram\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n \n Everywhere is cold jeeeez&#8230;.. I need someone here but am still a virgin. Let me just wait till my wedding night\nA post shared by  okuneye idris (@bobrisky222) on Oct 21, 2019 at 3:13am PDT\n\n\n\nThe post I&#8217;m Still A Virgin, Waiting For My Wedding Night: Bobrisky appeared first on Information Nigeria.\n', 0, 'Mon, 21 Oct 2019 13:45:18 +0000'),
(1379, 0, 'Highlands Park match is bigger than the Chiefs game – Mosimane', 'Sport', 'http://www.sabcnews.com/sabcnews/highlands-park-match-is-bigger-than-the-chiefs-game-mosimane/', 'http://www.sabcnews.com/sabcnews/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/SABC-News-Sundowns-Twitter-3.jpg', '<p><img width="756" height="426" src="http://www.sabcnews.com/sabcnews/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/SABC-News-Sundowns-Twitter-3.jpg" class="attachment-large size-large wp-post-image" alt="" style="margin-bottom: 15px;" srcset="http://www.sabcnews.com/sabcnews/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/SABC-News-Sundowns-Twitter-3.jpg 756w, http://www.sabcnews.com/sabcnews/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/SABC-News-Sundowns-Twitter-3-240x135.jpg 240w, http://www.sabcnews.com/sabcnews/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/SABC-News-Sundowns-Twitter-3-300x169.jpg 300w" sizes="(max-width: 756px) 100vw, 756px" /></p><p><a href="http://www.sabcnews.com/sabcnews/billiat-denies-approaching-mamelodi-sundowns/">Mamelodi Sundowns</a> will play against <a href="http://www.sabcnews.com/sabcnews/highlands-park-head-into-mtn-8-final-as-underdog/">Highlands Park</a> in a crucial league match at <a href="http://www.sabcnews.com/sabcnews/sundowns-likely-to-use-regular-players-in-caf-match/">Lucas Moripe Stadium</a> on Wednesday night.</p>\n<p>The game will be a pre-cursor to the big clash against arch-rivals <a href="http://www.sabcnews.com/sabcnews/kaizer-chiefs-golden-arrows-through-to-last-8-of-tko/">Kaizer Chiefs</a> at Loftus Versfeld Stadium on Sunday.</p>\n<p>The PSL champions are in third position with 14 points from six matches, behind log leaders Chiefs on 19 points from eight matches. Sundowns’ mentor <a href="http://www.sabcnews.com/sabcnews/we-need-to-learn-from-pitso-mosimane-komphela/">Pitso Mosimane</a> says the Highlands game is bigger than the Chiefs match.</p>\n<p>Sundowns were hammered 4-2 by Chiefs in the Shell Helix Cup clash at FNB stadium more than a week ago.</p>\n<p>The Brazilians were trailing 4-0 at half time but salvaged some pride with two goals in the second half. Mosimane says they do not need to beat Chiefs to win the league.</p>\n<p>The Brazilians drew 0-0 at Loftus in the first round last season, but won 1-0 at FNB stadium in the second round. Mosimane says they will not be emotional when they face Chiefs on Sunday.</p>\n<p>Midfielder Andile Jali had a good game in the middle of the park before he was substituted due to an injury.</p>\n<p>Jali has been struggling for game time in recent months but is slowly regaining his fitness and form. Mosimane says it is too early to talk about Bafana Bafana return. <strong><em>&#8211; Report by Vincent Sitsula</em></strong><br />\n<iframe src="https://embed.iono.fm/epi/760143" width="100%" height="135" frameborder="0"><a href="https://iono.fm/e/760143">Content hosted by iono.fm</a></iframe></p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.sabcnews.com/sabcnews/highlands-park-match-is-bigger-than-the-chiefs-game-mosimane/">Highlands Park match is bigger than the Chiefs game &#8211; Mosimane</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.sabcnews.com/sabcnews">SABC News - Breaking news, special reports, world, business, sport coverage of all South African current events. Africa&#039;s news leader.</a>.</p>\n', 0, 'Monday October 21, 2019'),
(1380, 0, 'Pirates players deserve some praise for clean sheet – Mokwena', 'Sport', 'http://www.sabcnews.com/sabcnews/pirates-players-deserve-some-praise-for-clean-sheet-mokwena/', 'http://www.sabcnews.com/sabcnews/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/SABC-News-Rhulani-Twitter.jpg', '<p><img width="756" height="426" src="http://www.sabcnews.com/sabcnews/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/SABC-News-Rhulani-Twitter.jpg" class="attachment-large size-large wp-post-image" alt="" style="margin-bottom: 15px;" srcset="http://www.sabcnews.com/sabcnews/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/SABC-News-Rhulani-Twitter.jpg 756w, http://www.sabcnews.com/sabcnews/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/SABC-News-Rhulani-Twitter-240x135.jpg 240w, http://www.sabcnews.com/sabcnews/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/SABC-News-Rhulani-Twitter-300x169.jpg 300w" sizes="(max-width: 756px) 100vw, 756px" /></p><p><a href="http://www.sabcnews.com/sabcnews/barker-feels-the-pressure-is-on-orlando-pirates-this-saturday/">Orlando Pirates</a> head coach <a href="http://www.sabcnews.com/sabcnews/i-am-prepared-to-die-for-orlando-pirates-mokwena/">Rhulani Mokwena</a> has defended his players for missing an avalanche of scoring chances this past weekend but still ended up beating <a href="http://www.sabcnews.com/sabcnews/stellenbosch-fc-record-a-maiden-absa-premiership-victory/">Stellenbosch FC</a> 1-0 in the <a href="http://www.sabcnews.com/sabcnews/telkom-knockout-last-16-dates-venues-kick-off-times-confirmed/">Telkom Knockout</a> last 16 match.</p>\n<p>Pirates needed a late winner from <a href="http://www.sabcnews.com/sabcnews/lorch-was-a-breath-of-fresh-air-in-bafana-line-up-manenzhe/">Thembinkosi Lorch</a> to seal their passage into the TKO quarterfinals.</p>\n<p>Coming to this game, they had scored eight goals in three matches and Mokwena says the focus should instead be on keeping a clean sheet, something they hadn’t done since August.</p>\n<p>Pirates have been playing an attractive brand of football and scoring goals but defending has been their key challenge having conceded seven goals in their last three matches.</p>\n<p>Mokwena reserved some special praise for his defense and was also happy with their high pressing game.</p>\n<p>. <strong><em>&#8211; Report by Velile Mnyandu </em></strong><br />\n<iframe src="https://embed.iono.fm/epi/760128" width="100%" height="135" frameborder="0"><a href="https://iono.fm/e/760128">Content hosted by iono.fm</a></iframe></p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.sabcnews.com/sabcnews/pirates-players-deserve-some-praise-for-clean-sheet-mokwena/">Pirates players deserve some praise for clean sheet &#8211; Mokwena</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.sabcnews.com/sabcnews">SABC News - Breaking news, special reports, world, business, sport coverage of all South African current events. Africa&#039;s news leader.</a>.</p>\n', 0, 'Monday October 21, 2019');
