(1381, 0, 'Referee Chavani displayed arrogance towards me – Komphela', 'Sport', 'http://www.sabcnews.com/sabcnews/referee-chavani-displayed-arrogance-towards-me-komphela/', 'http://www.sabcnews.com/sabcnews/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/SABC-News-Komphela-Twitter.jpg', '<p><img width="756" height="426" src="http://www.sabcnews.com/sabcnews/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/SABC-News-Komphela-Twitter.jpg" class="attachment-large size-large wp-post-image" alt="" style="margin-bottom: 15px;" srcset="http://www.sabcnews.com/sabcnews/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/SABC-News-Komphela-Twitter.jpg 756w, http://www.sabcnews.com/sabcnews/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/SABC-News-Komphela-Twitter-240x135.jpg 240w, http://www.sabcnews.com/sabcnews/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/SABC-News-Komphela-Twitter-300x169.jpg 300w" sizes="(max-width: 756px) 100vw, 756px" /></p><p><a href="http://www.sabcnews.com/sabcnews/komphela-on-axed-coaches-and-building-towards-arrows-next-game/">Lamontville Golden Arrows</a> coach <a href="http://www.sabcnews.com/sabcnews/steve-komphela-pressure-win-important-games/">Steve Komphela</a> has lambasted young referee Jelly Chavani for being disrespectful during their <a href="http://www.sabcnews.com/sabcnews/telkom-knockout-last-16-dates-venues-kick-off-times-confirmed/">Telkom Knockout</a> fixture against Polokwane City over the weekend.</p>\n<p>The 23-year-old yellow carded the Abafana Bes’thende boss for leaving his designated area on the touchline a few times and also sarcastically asked him if he wants to take the whistle.</p>\n<p>This irritated Komphela and he says Chavani, who has vast experience from refereeing lower levels of the game, needs to be better than that when he deals with players and officials in the Premier Soccer League (PSL).</p>\n<p>Arrows won the game 1-0 at the Sugar Ray Xulu Stadium in Clermont, progressing to the quarter-finals of the annual tournament after an additional 30 minutes of extra time were needed.</p>\n<p>However, Chavani’s moment of madness for Komphela happened early on during the game, which left the former Free State Stars and <a href="http://www.sabcnews.com/sabcnews/kaizer-chiefs-golden-arrows-through-to-last-8-of-tko/">Kaizer Chiefs</a> coach visibly upset on the sidelines. He says he cannot tolerate such behaviour.</p>\n<p>Chavani began refereeing in the <a href="http://www.sabcnews.com/sabcnews/tshakhuma-tsha-madzuvhandila-dismiss-coach/">GladAfrica Championship</a> during the 2015/16 campaign. A season later (2016/17), the official from Chavani Village in Limpopo, was given the nod to officiate in PSL matches as well and was involved in five league games.</p>\n<p>Despite his quick rise up the ranks, he still needs to stay humble, according to Komphela.<strong><em> &#8211; </em></strong><strong><em>Report by Thahir Asmal</em></strong><br />\n<iframe src="https://embed.iono.fm/epi/760108" width="100%" height="135" frameborder="0"><a href="https://iono.fm/e/760108">Content hosted by iono.fm</a></iframe></p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.sabcnews.com/sabcnews/referee-chavani-displayed-arrogance-towards-me-komphela/">Referee Chavani displayed arrogance towards me &#8211; Komphela</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.sabcnews.com/sabcnews">SABC News - Breaking news, special reports, world, business, sport coverage of all South African current events. Africa&#039;s news leader.</a>.</p>\n', 0, 'Monday October 21, 2019'),
(1382, 0, 'C Town City look to bounce back against Maritzburg', 'Sport', 'http://www.sabcnews.com/sabcnews/c-town-city-look-to-bounce-back-against-maritzburg/', 'http://www.sabcnews.com/sabcnews/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/SABC-News-CT-City-Twitter-1.jpg', '<p><img width="756" height="426" src="http://www.sabcnews.com/sabcnews/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/SABC-News-CT-City-Twitter-1.jpg" class="attachment-large size-large wp-post-image" alt="" style="margin-bottom: 15px;" srcset="http://www.sabcnews.com/sabcnews/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/SABC-News-CT-City-Twitter-1.jpg 756w, http://www.sabcnews.com/sabcnews/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/SABC-News-CT-City-Twitter-1-240x135.jpg 240w, http://www.sabcnews.com/sabcnews/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/SABC-News-CT-City-Twitter-1-300x169.jpg 300w" sizes="(max-width: 756px) 100vw, 756px" /></p><p><a href="http://www.sabcnews.com/sabcnews/cape-town-city-players-aims-to-outplay-chiefs-in-tko/">Cape Town City</a> will look to bounce back this Friday when they host <a href="http://www.sabcnews.com/sabcnews/time-needed-to-fix-maritzburg-united-shortcomings-tinkler/">Maritzburg United</a> in a Absa Premiership game, looking for just their second win of their league campaign.</p>\n<p>City lost on penalties to <a href="http://www.sabcnews.com/sabcnews/kaizer-chiefs-golden-arrows-through-to-last-8-of-tko/">Kaizer Chiefs</a> in the <a href="http://www.sabcnews.com/sabcnews/telkom-knockout-last-16-dates-venues-kick-off-times-confirmed/">Telkom Knockout</a> this weekend.</p>\n<p>Five draws have helped City to tenth spot, while Maritzburg are just behind them in 11<sup>th</sup> position.</p>\n<p>However City coach <a href="http://www.sabcnews.com/sabcnews/i-wanted-arsenal-to-sign-benni-mccarthy-wright/">Benni McCarthy</a> is confident that if they play like they did against Chiefs they can get a result against Maritzburg.</p>\n<p>McCarthy says there were a lot of positives to take away from the 4-2 penalty loss to Chiefs. The teams had drawn 1-1 in regulation, after Samir Nurkovic’s late goal cancelled out Kermit Erasmus’ earlier strike and McCarthy feels his team did not take their chances.</p>\n<p>A notable absentee from the City team was captain Thami Mkhize. McCarthy says Mkhize, who is set to make his 100th appearance for the club, has only just started training again, since getting injured against AmaZulu FC before the international break.</p>\n<p>Meanwhile City have confirmed they have extended Dutch goalkeeper Peter Leeuwenburgh’s contract until 2023.</p>\n<p>Having joined City at the start of last season, Leeuwenburgh feels he made the right decision in joining the club.</p>\n<p><iframe src="https://embed.iono.fm/epi/760104" width="100%" height="135" frameborder="0"><a href="https://iono.fm/e/760104">Content hosted by iono.fm</a></iframe></p>\n<p><strong><em>&#8211; Report by Rob Delport</em></strong></p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.sabcnews.com/sabcnews/c-town-city-look-to-bounce-back-against-maritzburg/">C Town City look to bounce back against Maritzburg</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.sabcnews.com/sabcnews">SABC News - Breaking news, special reports, world, business, sport coverage of all South African current events. Africa&#039;s news leader.</a>.</p>\n', 0, 'Monday October 21, 2019'),
(1383, 0, 'Erasmus says in-depth Welsh team knowledge will be handy', 'Sport', 'http://www.sabcnews.com/sabcnews/erasmus-says-in-depth-welsh-team-knowledge-will-be-handy/', 'http://www.sabcnews.com/sabcnews/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/SABC-News-Springboks-Twitter-2.jpg', '<p><img width="756" height="426" src="http://www.sabcnews.com/sabcnews/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/SABC-News-Springboks-Twitter-2.jpg" class="attachment-large size-large wp-post-image" alt="" style="margin-bottom: 15px;" srcset="http://www.sabcnews.com/sabcnews/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/SABC-News-Springboks-Twitter-2.jpg 756w, http://www.sabcnews.com/sabcnews/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/SABC-News-Springboks-Twitter-2-240x135.jpg 240w, http://www.sabcnews.com/sabcnews/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/SABC-News-Springboks-Twitter-2-300x169.jpg 300w" sizes="(max-width: 756px) 100vw, 756px" /></p><p><a href="http://www.sabcnews.com/sabcnews/springboks-advance-to-semifinals-to-face-wales-in-rwc2019/">Springboks</a> coach <a href="http://www.sabcnews.com/sabcnews/rassie-erasmus-confirmed-new-springboks-coach/">Rassie Erasmus</a> believes that knowing the Wales’ intricate style of rugby well will definitely be an advantage for the Springboks heading into their <a href="http://www.sabcnews.com/sabcnews/two-rugby-world-cup-matches-cancelled-ahead-of-typhoon-hagibis/">Rugby World Cup</a> semifinal clash this weekend.</p>\n<p>Having coached in the European leagues for more than five years before returning to the helm of the Springboks, Erasmus says that his in-depth knowledge of Welsh teams will come in handy.<br />\n<iframe src="https://embed.iono.fm/epi/760120" width="100%" height="135" frameborder="0"><a href="https://iono.fm/e/760120">Content hosted by iono.fm</a></iframe><br />\nHaving lost to Wales twice since taking over as the head coach of the Springboks, Erasmus remains confident that the Boks should have the edge over them.</p>\n<p>The Springboks on Sunday overcame a spirited Japanese side to book their place in the next round of the tournament with a well-deserved 26-3 denying the hosts any tries in the process.</p>\n<p>The Boks have scored the most points of the tournament thus far and they have only conceded three tries in five games to date. Erasmus emphasised the importance of their defense.</p>\n<p>The Boks went into the half time break leading 11-3 with Japan sniffing the upset following an early injury and a yellow card to pro forward <a href="http://www.sabcnews.com/sabcnews/erasmus-shuffles-line-up-ahead-of-sa-italy-showdown/">Beast Mtawarira</a> in the first half.</p>\n<p>Erasmus says they expected everything Japan threw at them and they are happy they could neutralise it all in the second half.</p>\n<p>Having gone into the game with a four-two split amongst the forwards and the backs, Boks captain <a href="http://www.sabcnews.com/sabcnews/siya-kolisi-to-captain-sprinboks-in-the-final-warm-up/">Siya Kolisi</a> lauded the substitutes bench for their impact when they came on. He adds that there are no egos about it either. <strong><em>&#8211; Report by Thando Gqamane</em></strong><br />\n<iframe src="https://embed.iono.fm/epi/760124" width="100%" height="135" frameborder="0"><a href="https://iono.fm/e/760124">Content hosted by iono.fm</a></iframe></p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.sabcnews.com/sabcnews/erasmus-says-in-depth-welsh-team-knowledge-will-be-handy/">Erasmus says in-depth Welsh team knowledge will be handy</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.sabcnews.com/sabcnews">SABC News - Breaking news, special reports, world, business, sport coverage of all South African current events. Africa&#039;s news leader.</a>.</p>\n', 0, 'Monday October 21, 2019'),
(1384, 0, 'Molokwane named as new president of Netball Africa', 'Sport', 'http://www.sabcnews.com/sabcnews/molokwane-named-as-new-president-of-netball-africa/', 'http://www.sabcnews.com/sabcnews/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/SABC-News-Cecilia-Molokwane-Twitter.jpg', '<p><img width="756" height="426" src="http://www.sabcnews.com/sabcnews/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/SABC-News-Cecilia-Molokwane-Twitter.jpg" class="attachment-large size-large wp-post-image" alt="" style="margin-bottom: 15px;" srcset="http://www.sabcnews.com/sabcnews/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/SABC-News-Cecilia-Molokwane-Twitter.jpg 756w, http://www.sabcnews.com/sabcnews/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/SABC-News-Cecilia-Molokwane-Twitter-240x135.jpg 240w, http://www.sabcnews.com/sabcnews/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/SABC-News-Cecilia-Molokwane-Twitter-300x169.jpg 300w" sizes="(max-width: 756px) 100vw, 756px" /></p><p><a href="http://www.sabcnews.com/sabcnews/netball-south-africa-announces-team-for-2019-world-cup/">Netball South Africa</a> President <a href="http://www.sabcnews.com/sabcnews/molokwane-happy-with-the-success-of-the-spar-national-championship/">Cecilia Molokwane</a> has been named the new president of <a href="http://www.sabcnews.com/sabcnews/chauke-laments-lack-of-enough-time-to-prepare-for-africa-netball-cup/">Netball Africa</a>.</p>\n<p>Molokwane was named to the hot seat at the end of last week, and will also serve as the International Netball Federation’s Director for Africa.</p>\n<p>She replaces Botswana’s Tebogo Lebotse Sebago who stepped down earlier this month. Molokwane says it has been an overwhelming year for her and she is very proud to take on this new role.</p>\n<p>Molokwane says she is a woman of action rather than making promises, she would like to hit the ground running in this new role.</p>\n<p>Molokwane is very proud of the growth of netball’s profile over the past year, and especially South Africa’s performance at the Netball World Cup in Liverpool.</p>\n<p>Cape Town is currently hosting the <a href="http://www.sabcnews.com/sabcnews/chauke-laments-lack-of-enough-time-to-prepare-for-africa-netball-cup/">Africa Netball Cup</a>, and Molokwane explains why they stepped in to host after Zimbabwe withdrew.</p>\n<p><iframe src="https://embed.iono.fm/epi/759993" width="100%" height="135" frameborder="0"><a href="https://iono.fm/e/759993">Content hosted by iono.fm</a></iframe></p>\n<p>After this event that ends on the 22nd of October, Cape Town will host more netball action next month when South Africa hosts England in a three match series. <strong><em>&#8211; Report by Rob Delport</em></strong></p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.sabcnews.com/sabcnews/molokwane-named-as-new-president-of-netball-africa/">Molokwane named as new president of Netball Africa</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.sabcnews.com/sabcnews">SABC News - Breaking news, special reports, world, business, sport coverage of all South African current events. Africa&#039;s news leader.</a>.</p>\n', 0, 'Monday October 21, 2019'),
